WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:15.300 --> 00:00:20.180
﻿Vujo, good afternoon. It is a great
pleasure to have you here with me.

00:00:20.460 --> 00:00:22.460
Finally someone
who played my sport.

00:00:22.700 --> 00:00:27.060
Thank you for your time.
I want to say the same thing.

00:00:28.100 --> 00:00:32.980
If someone had told me a few years ago
that I would have an interview with you,

00:00:33.340 --> 00:00:35.300
I wouldn't have believed it.

00:00:35.540 --> 00:00:39.220
I've seen a few shows. I must say
that you are doing it very well.

00:00:39.500 --> 00:00:43.500
You are showing talent not only
in handball but also as a presenter.

00:00:43.607 --> 00:00:47.327
It is my great honor and pleasure
to be your guest. -Thanks, Vujo.

00:00:47.448 --> 00:00:49.528
Thank you very much.

00:00:50.140 --> 00:00:59.940
Let's go back to your childhood
and your career, which was special.

00:01:00.220 --> 00:01:04.820
Both as a player and as a coach,
but let’s go back to the beginning.

00:01:05.060 --> 00:01:10.700
You were born in 1961 in Cetinje.
-In January, when it's the coldest.

00:01:11.780 --> 00:01:18.848
Cetinje is a specific city,
so what was your upbringing like?

00:01:19.168 --> 00:01:23.248
What were the living
conditions like?

00:01:24.875 --> 00:01:30.359
It was a different time, I assume
other guest on the show said the same.

00:01:31.500 --> 00:01:36.500
There was no internet, mobile phones
and everything that today,

00:01:36.780 --> 00:01:40.340
as much as it helps us,
at the same time spoils the youth.

00:01:41.100 --> 00:01:46.180
At that time, all the children in Cetinje
were involved in some kind of sport.

00:01:47.620 --> 00:01:51.340
The first sport I started
practicing was karate.

00:01:53.020 --> 00:01:57.540
Karate is a good supplementary
sport for all other sports.

00:01:58.060 --> 00:02:07.940
Develops personality, discipline,
character. Coordination too.

00:02:08.940 --> 00:02:14.860
Practicing karate, I got a blue belt.
I studied with the Jorga brothers.

00:02:15.100 --> 00:02:20.964
They were famous karate fighters.
One of them was called Ilija.

00:02:21.109 --> 00:02:23.448
Forgot the others name.

00:02:25.380 --> 00:02:31.820
It was a great supplementary sport.
But I always preferred team sports.

00:02:33.740 --> 00:02:39.260
My older brother noticed
that the basketball club Lovćen

00:02:39.820 --> 00:02:42.660
is enrolling new members.

00:02:43.020 --> 00:02:47.380
Such a poster was in all schools
that Lovćen was enrolling new members.

00:02:47.620 --> 00:02:52.740
I went there with my brother,
and there were fifty children there.

00:02:52.980 --> 00:02:56.260
They gave us the ball there
and we just shot.

00:02:56.900 --> 00:03:01.540
When the training ended,
they told my brother

00:03:01.780 --> 00:03:05.700
to come to the training on
Monday, and they thanked me.

00:03:05.900 --> 00:03:08.660
It was a big
disappointment for me.

00:03:09.180 --> 00:03:12.780
First, I can't play basketball,
and secondly that my brother

00:03:13.020 --> 00:03:16.980
was better than me.
I couldn't admit that.

00:03:19.660 --> 00:03:23.100
Then I continued practicing karate.

00:03:24.500 --> 00:03:29.700
According to the old education system,
I was in the 7th or 8th grade.

00:03:30.020 --> 00:03:34.340
Friends from school asked me
to come and play

00:03:34.540 --> 00:03:38.300
in the school handball championship.

00:03:38.540 --> 00:03:41.460
I asked them what they
were talking about,

00:03:41.700 --> 00:03:46.380
I neither know how to play that sport
nor do I know what it is about.

00:03:47.604 --> 00:03:51.604
But for some reason, I didn't have
anything better to do that day,

00:03:52.820 --> 00:04:01.540
I got on my bike, and since
I had outgrown my jeans pants,

00:04:01.870 --> 00:04:04.775
my mother shortened my bottoms.

00:04:05.180 --> 00:04:09.140
It was some kind of shorts.
I went to the game too.

00:04:09.500 --> 00:04:15.380
And they were missing one player.
I parked my bike and jumped the fence.

00:04:15.820 --> 00:04:20.380
And that day we won.
And to me, victory is everything.

00:04:20.900 --> 00:04:28.300
Even today when I play board games
with my friends, cards with my wife.

00:04:28.500 --> 00:04:33.096
I don't care at all if I stole the joker,
I just want to win.

00:04:34.420 --> 00:04:36.980
So the phrase the most important thing
is to participate doesn't exist with you.

00:04:37.415 --> 00:04:40.927
That's right.
-But just how to win.

00:04:41.580 --> 00:04:47.091
We won that game.
That tournament is over.

00:04:48.580 --> 00:04:53.820
And Miško Popović, the best coach
in the history of Montenegrin sports,

00:04:54.580 --> 00:05:00.020
came with a lot of authority
and didn't ask me if I wanted it or not.

00:05:00.260 --> 00:05:03.980
He just told me: "Boy, come
to training on Monday at 6 p.m."

00:05:04.220 --> 00:05:07.380
I was shocked.
Because I couldn't say no.

00:05:07.580 --> 00:05:10.620
It doesn't exist.

00:05:12.500 --> 00:05:15.500
Handball players were
the pride of the city.

00:05:15.780 --> 00:05:18.940
They played in
the second federal league.

00:05:19.180 --> 00:05:22.468
They played the Yugoslavian Cup,
so big teams came to Cetinje,

00:05:22.568 --> 00:05:24.648
and they had hard time.

00:05:25.973 --> 00:05:31.230
Clubs like Lovćen,
Goražde, Bitola.

00:05:31.580 --> 00:05:34.260
These were all clubs
from the second league,

00:05:34.500 --> 00:05:37.700
but the victory in Cetinje
meant a lot to them.

00:05:38.020 --> 00:05:42.900
So I start training handball,
but in that year I grew quite a bit.

00:05:43.980 --> 00:05:49.780
It is the period when children grow.
And I was even bigger than my brother.

00:05:49.980 --> 00:05:57.140
One day my brother came and said
that the basketball coaches

00:05:57.460 --> 00:06:02.460
invited me to come to practice.
-An old ailment is back.

00:06:03.140 --> 00:06:07.580
There is no way I can balance
karate, basketball and handball.

00:06:07.820 --> 00:06:13.100
I went to handball training first,
and then basketball.

00:06:13.380 --> 00:06:19.220
Then both clubs registered
me for the first team.

00:06:21.620 --> 00:06:24.940
So how did you manage to coordinate
the training sessions?

00:06:25.460 --> 00:06:28.340
There was one small gym in Cetinje,

00:06:28.540 --> 00:06:32.580
then they trained
in different periods of time.

00:06:32.820 --> 00:06:37.824
Or the handball players would train
outside on the concrete playground,

00:06:37.958 --> 00:06:39.758
during the day.

00:06:39.982 --> 00:06:43.684
And then the basketball players
would train in the hall in the evening.

00:06:43.806 --> 00:06:48.902
Neither one nor the other knew
that I train both sports.

00:06:51.660 --> 00:06:54.140
However, the first problems appear.

00:06:54.420 --> 00:06:57.100
Let's say when handball players
would play in Bitola,

00:06:58.300 --> 00:07:01.460
and basketball players
in Bijelo Polje.

00:07:02.887 --> 00:07:10.022
Where should I go? Then the coaches
would agree where I should go.

00:07:10.388 --> 00:07:14.075
I used to come back from Bitola
at 4 a.m., and these others play

00:07:14.216 --> 00:07:16.216
in Bijelo Polje at 10 a.m.

00:07:16.463 --> 00:07:18.783
And they start their journey at 6 a.m.

00:07:19.043 --> 00:07:22.003
Then a whole busload of players
would come to wake me up.

00:07:22.267 --> 00:07:25.689
I often didn't even know
where we were playing,

00:07:25.931 --> 00:07:29.876
because I slept
while we were traveling.

00:07:31.380 --> 00:07:38.180
I played both basketball and handball
for many years. -What years were those?

00:07:39.989 --> 00:07:43.020
Until I was 16 or 17.
-That's already serious.

00:07:43.202 --> 00:07:45.231
I played like that until
16 or 17 years old.

00:07:45.428 --> 00:07:51.044
The problem was not only that
there were other athletes from Ulcinj

00:07:51.298 --> 00:07:57.278
Podgorica, Tivat who also played
basketball and handball.

00:07:57.700 --> 00:08:00.700
It often happened that we met
at a basketball game on Saturday

00:08:00.940 --> 00:08:04.180
and at a handball game on Sunday.

00:08:04.460 --> 00:08:09.020
I remember from Tivat Boško and
Čečun were fantastic basketball

00:08:09.260 --> 00:08:11.620
and handball players.

00:08:13.780 --> 00:08:20.774
At that time, sport was available
to everyone and there was no interest,

00:08:21.300 --> 00:08:25.580
no money, and no big careers
were thought about.

00:08:28.940 --> 00:08:34.260
We always suffered criticism from
our parents because they buy sneakers,

00:08:34.500 --> 00:08:41.180
and when you play on tarmac,
you quickly tear them.

00:08:42.340 --> 00:08:45.420
Then we shouldn't have asked
for new ones, rather,

00:08:45.660 --> 00:08:50.180
you would cut a cardboard mold
and put it inside a tennis shoe,

00:08:50.380 --> 00:08:53.660
but that too would wear out and all that
would be left was a hole in the sock.

00:08:53.900 --> 00:08:58.300
Mother would then say: "How long
will you train, when will you stop."

00:08:59.300 --> 00:09:05.180
We had a real fight, whether
to continue or give up the sport.

00:09:05.580 --> 00:09:07.860
But fortunately I continued
to play sports.

00:09:08.100 --> 00:09:13.300
Do you think that basketball
and training helped you achieve

00:09:13.540 --> 00:09:17.740
good results in handball as well?

00:09:17.980 --> 00:09:24.620
What do you think would have happened
if you had continued playing basketball?

00:09:24.820 --> 00:09:28.980
Would you perhaps achieve
as good results as in handball?

00:09:29.180 --> 00:09:33.100
I've never had a problem
with two-step or three-step.

00:09:33.300 --> 00:09:37.020
I've never made the mistake of being
stopped by the referee for that.

00:09:37.260 --> 00:09:42.740
I understood the difference
between the sports very quickly.

00:09:42.980 --> 00:09:47.140
Basketball helped me to play better,
to have better combinatorics

00:09:47.380 --> 00:09:54.300
in a smaller space and in movement.
That later helped me in handball as well.

00:09:56.980 --> 00:10:04.980
I received an invitation from KK Bosna,
European champion to join their ranks.

00:10:07.980 --> 00:10:15.220
There was a basketball coach who was
on loan in KK Mornar from Bar,

00:10:15.420 --> 00:10:19.660
so he watched our games
and me as a basketball player.

00:10:20.980 --> 00:10:23.820
At the same time,
I received an invitation from

00:10:24.100 --> 00:10:27.700
Yugoslav junior handball team.

00:10:28.540 --> 00:10:31.420
I didn't know what to do.

00:10:31.780 --> 00:10:37.500
I thought about it and said that I wanted
to meet Jurin, Rađenović, Krivokapić.

00:10:37.740 --> 00:10:40.540
To make sure if they are
men made od flesh and blood.

00:10:40.740 --> 00:10:44.620
I wanted to touch them because
they were the role models I dreamed of.

00:10:44.820 --> 00:10:48.180
First I dreamed and later I played
with them and won medals.

00:10:48.380 --> 00:10:51.660
So that ruled in favor of handball?

00:10:51.900 --> 00:10:56.333
When I appeared in Pula,
all the clubs from the Yugoslav

00:10:56.487 --> 00:10:59.982
first league wanted me
to play for them.

00:11:01.127 --> 00:11:05.091
That's when Goran Nerić appeared,
who was a junior member

00:11:06.008 --> 00:11:09.365
of the Yugoslav national team,
and played for Željezničar from Sarajevo.

00:11:09.642 --> 00:11:13.341
He had a conversation with me
and told me that it would be good

00:11:13.469 --> 00:11:15.669
for me to come to Željezničar
because it is a big club,

00:11:15.833 --> 00:11:18.033
and Sarajevo is an excellent city.

00:11:18.180 --> 00:11:21.550
Then I thought I'd go,
and if I don't succeed in handball,

00:11:21.776 --> 00:11:25.846
I will certainly have an invitation
from KK Bosna, so I can try basketball.

00:11:26.142 --> 00:11:32.612
And if I fail in that too, I'll go back
and assemble washing machines.

00:11:33.464 --> 00:11:40.391
Back then, Obod was a big factory.

00:11:43.860 --> 00:11:51.100
But there was something
I hadn't realized I said.

00:11:51.580 --> 00:11:56.140
And that is that Veselin Vuković
is also Montenegrin,

00:11:56.380 --> 00:12:00.340
his father is a military person
and we hung out at that gathering.

00:12:00.540 --> 00:12:06.960
He convinced me to come to Šabac.
I couldn't believe what he was saying.

00:12:07.398 --> 00:12:10.327
He wanted me to promise him
that I would come to Šabac.

00:12:10.526 --> 00:12:12.166
I told him to leave me alone.

00:12:12.336 --> 00:12:15.327
Later we were at a party one night
and I told him I would come.

00:12:15.460 --> 00:12:20.060
He demanded that I promise.
And I promised him.

00:12:20.460 --> 00:12:29.580
When I promised Nerić, I remembered
that I had promised Vuković the same.

00:12:30.500 --> 00:12:32.300
What should I do now?

00:12:32.580 --> 00:12:35.380
In the morning at breakfast I said
I regret that I will not come

00:12:35.620 --> 00:12:38.420
to Sarajevo and I asked him
to apologize to the people.

00:12:38.660 --> 00:12:43.480
He asked why. I couldn't explain
to him any further.

00:12:44.060 --> 00:12:49.860
So it ended and each of us went home.
But we forgot to exchange phone numbers.

00:12:50.980 --> 00:12:52.660
And then what did Vuković do?

00:12:52.940 --> 00:12:56.180
He took the telephone
directory of Cetinje.

00:12:56.540 --> 00:13:01.500
He was looking for the Vujović.
And there are many of them in Cetinje.

00:13:02.140 --> 00:13:09.140
He called and asked people if anyone
in their family was involved in sports.

00:13:09.380 --> 00:13:10.980
They would say no.

00:13:11.220 --> 00:13:15.260
And if you know any of your relatives,
they would answer that they don't know.

00:13:15.500 --> 00:13:18.460
He called one, another, a fifth,
and finally one of them said

00:13:18.700 --> 00:13:23.460
that Krsto's boy was playing something,
both brothers practice something.

00:13:23.660 --> 00:13:26.220
He asked if they knew the number
and they gave it to him.

00:13:26.420 --> 00:13:29.900
One day the phone rang
and I answered, and he said:

00:13:30.100 --> 00:13:33.420
"Vujo, where are you?"

00:13:35.035 --> 00:13:36.904
I asked who was calling me.
He says: "Vuk".

00:13:37.102 --> 00:13:40.412
I've been looking for you for years.
He asked me if I was normal.

00:13:40.597 --> 00:13:46.623
He asked me if the deal was still valid.
I told him I have a club.

00:13:47.206 --> 00:13:51.154
He told me that their representative,
Aca Trifunović,

00:13:52.660 --> 00:13:55.716
who is Don Vito Corleone
in the job, will come.

00:13:55.868 --> 00:13:58.162
That's what we called him.

00:13:58.282 --> 00:14:00.482
He was ahead of his time
and created a great generation.

00:14:00.620 --> 00:14:02.620
He was the alpha and
omega of Metaloplastika.

00:14:02.782 --> 00:14:10.373
Anyone who has not met him has lost
a lot in life. He was a monster.

00:14:12.300 --> 00:14:17.740
But the administration and people
from Lovćen were angry

00:14:17.980 --> 00:14:23.980
because someone is coming to
Montenegro to take players away.

00:14:24.260 --> 00:14:28.100
They said he should be ashamed
of what he is doing.

00:14:28.340 --> 00:14:35.620
I told him it wouldn't be easy.
But here comes Don Vito Corleone.

00:14:35.860 --> 00:14:40.260
He threw his coat over his shoulder,
he arrived by plane,

00:14:40.460 --> 00:14:44.540
a car was waiting at the airport.
He comes to our house.

00:14:44.820 --> 00:14:49.060
He gave 100 DM to my mother,
100 DM to my sister,

00:14:49.260 --> 00:14:51.580
and a bottle of whiskey
for my father.

00:14:51.860 --> 00:14:56.420
And salaries at that time were 200 DM.
They didn't know what was going on.

00:14:58.300 --> 00:15:03.380
He said he came because of me.
Father asked: "For whom"?

00:15:03.900 --> 00:15:06.540
Aco says: "Because of Veselin".

00:15:06.820 --> 00:15:09.780
Where did you come from?
-From Šabac.

00:15:10.500 --> 00:15:14.900
You came from Šabac to Cetinje
because of my son? -Yes.

00:15:15.460 --> 00:15:19.700
You came all the way for him?
-Well, yes.

00:15:20.300 --> 00:15:25.740
So, is he that good?
-He is the best. -Who is the best?

00:15:26.420 --> 00:15:28.140
Well, your son.

00:15:28.340 --> 00:15:30.420
My father told me to come to him.

00:15:30.820 --> 00:15:35.220
That was the moment
of the greatest love he showed me.

00:15:35.420 --> 00:15:38.300
He grabbed my hair and asked: "How
come I don't know anything about it".

00:15:38.500 --> 00:15:40.380
I just kept quiet.

00:15:40.620 --> 00:15:45.300
The first part was successfully
completed, but now we need to talk

00:15:45.460 --> 00:15:47.660
to the administration of Lovćen.

00:15:48.620 --> 00:15:53.820
There were all present, chairman
of the committee and everyone else.

00:15:54.100 --> 00:15:59.420
Everyone looked at us strangely.
Aco came and greeted them all nicely.

00:15:59.620 --> 00:16:02.700
Before they said anything,
he said the following.

00:16:02.980 --> 00:16:09.380
I know how well you work
and how you work with these children.

00:16:09.580 --> 00:16:12.380
Congratulations to you,
you are phenomenal.

00:16:12.620 --> 00:16:16.860
I will give you five million
dinars in compensation,

00:16:17.060 --> 00:16:20.980
and I will also give you five million
for him in equipment.

00:16:21.700 --> 00:16:25.420
All honor to you, so to speak,
you are excellent.

00:16:25.700 --> 00:16:30.660
So I am the first player in history
to be compensated.

00:16:30.860 --> 00:16:35.900
Compensation. They sold me easily.

00:16:36.540 --> 00:16:41.460
They sold me easily.
After that, I went to Šabac.

00:16:41.740 --> 00:16:45.620
After 10 million dinars,
Vuja could go.

00:16:45.860 --> 00:16:49.340
It was not a small sum of money.
-I believe not.

00:16:49.540 --> 00:16:55.660
My only condition was
to buy a car Zastava 101.

00:16:55.940 --> 00:17:00.700
I thought when I sat in that car,

00:17:01.020 --> 00:17:04.020
no one would be
more important than me.

00:17:04.260 --> 00:17:08.540
My father was a chauffeur
or rather a professional driver.

00:17:08.740 --> 00:17:11.340
He drove all his life.

00:17:12.060 --> 00:17:18.970
When he was away I would
always sleep on his pillow,

00:17:19.719 --> 00:17:22.666
because it smelled
of oil and gasoline.

00:17:23.420 --> 00:17:28.260
Because I missed him so much,
and I was not aware of it.

00:17:30.780 --> 00:17:33.260
Life was hard at that time.

00:17:33.620 --> 00:17:38.860
There were five of us in the house,
and only my father worked.

00:17:41.700 --> 00:17:44.020
We somehow survived.

00:17:44.340 --> 00:17:47.913
I remember that flour was transported
by train from Bačka Palanka

00:17:48.036 --> 00:17:49.836
to the port of Bar.

00:17:50.387 --> 00:17:52.627
My mother would sometimes
say to ny father:

00:17:52.750 --> 00:17:55.968
"Krsto, can you steal a bag of flour?”

00:17:56.429 --> 00:17:59.709
What will happen if someone
sees me doing this?

00:18:00.098 --> 00:18:02.898
I didn't understand what
that meant at the time.

00:18:03.186 --> 00:18:08.946
Only later did I understand his words.
And I always remembered that.

00:18:10.260 --> 00:18:19.260
Not to embarrass the family.
Times are different today.

00:18:19.820 --> 00:18:23.380
When someone goes to prison,
the family prepares a party for him

00:18:23.462 --> 00:18:25.121
as if he was going to the army.

00:18:25.245 --> 00:18:27.816
What used to be a shame,
today people are proud of it.

00:18:27.985 --> 00:18:29.905
Unfortunately, but that's how it is.

00:18:35.180 --> 00:18:40.900
Do you think that the mentality
of people from Cetinje

00:18:41.322 --> 00:18:46.281
helped you reach those
heights during your career?

00:18:46.606 --> 00:18:53.000
Do you think it is an important
part of your career?

00:18:54.232 --> 00:18:56.679
I don't know if you met
anyone Cetinje,

00:18:56.940 --> 00:19:00.580
maybe Petar Kapisoda or
Goran Đukanović? -Yes, I did.

00:19:01.860 --> 00:19:08.100
They're quick thinking people
and have above-average intelligence.

00:19:08.420 --> 00:19:16.220
Look, maybe people from Nikšić and
Berane talk about themselves this way,

00:19:16.740 --> 00:19:22.940
but I'm speaking from my experience.
When you talk about Cetinje,

00:19:23.260 --> 00:19:25.620
or if you ask someone where they're
from, they might say Podgorica,

00:19:25.860 --> 00:19:30.460
Nikšić, or Tivat. But when you
ask someone from Cetinje,

00:19:30.700 --> 00:19:35.380
they'll tell you with an air of pride
as if they're above everyone else.

00:19:35.700 --> 00:19:41.780
Just from that, you're coming
from a place of power.

00:19:43.540 --> 00:19:47.860
Cetinje has a history engraved
in stone foundations.

00:19:48.180 --> 00:19:51.100
It was the capital.
-It was the capital.

00:19:51.380 --> 00:19:56.620
"This rock here is where this person
died," "Here we killed a Turk,"

00:19:56.980 --> 00:20:00.420
"Here is where that battle was held."

00:20:00.820 --> 00:20:04.460
Everything is history,
everything is written down,

00:20:04.700 --> 00:20:07.860
and all those details teach you
which path you should take,

00:20:08.100 --> 00:20:10.380
and that you have to be the best.

00:20:10.740 --> 00:20:15.460
Average is not acceptable, and neither
is bad, and this is made crystal clear.

00:20:15.700 --> 00:20:19.100
The people there have
a specific type of humor.

00:20:19.340 --> 00:20:25.860
My village, Mikulići, not too many years
ago, got access to electricity.

00:20:26.380 --> 00:20:30.540
And the rascals from Cetinje were
sitting around, and one of them asked,

00:20:30.740 --> 00:20:34.060
"Hey, did you hear
Mikulići got electricity?"

00:20:34.260 --> 00:20:40.620
Another says, "Now you'll hear the
complaining, moaning, and crying there."

00:20:40.820 --> 00:20:44.780
They ask him why, and he says
"They're about to find out Tito died."

00:20:46.460 --> 00:20:49.860
That's how remote and obscure
location of my village is.

00:20:50.100 --> 00:20:53.380
Just imagine who would come up
with something like that.

00:20:53.620 --> 00:20:57.220
Or there is that one story of how a
person from Cetinje leaves the table.

00:20:57.420 --> 00:21:00.940
He makes sure his cigarettes and lighter
stay on the table because if he doesn't,

00:21:01.180 --> 00:21:04.660
the others will start gossiping about
him, but if he leaves them there,

00:21:04.860 --> 00:21:08.740
the people will think he's going to
come back, so they won't even begin.

00:21:08.980 --> 00:21:16.660
I have to say that that mentality,
way of thinking, and way of life...

00:21:18.820 --> 00:21:23.464
Everywhere else in the world
when a kid falls and hurts himself,

00:21:23.823 --> 00:21:27.791
gets a bruised knee or an elbow,
the parents ask the kid

00:21:28.083 --> 00:21:32.425
"Did you hurt yourself? Are you in
pain?" But here, my father would say

00:21:33.140 --> 00:21:37.620
"Why don't you look where you're going?
Do you want me to smack you?

00:21:37.860 --> 00:21:41.460
I hope you break your leg next time."
You wouldn't even tell anyone

00:21:41.660 --> 00:21:45.060
that you fell, it hurts, or anything
about it. You have to push through it

00:21:45.300 --> 00:21:49.340
with your tongue behind your teeth.
That toughens you up from an early age.

00:21:49.580 --> 00:21:53.220
That mentality definitely helped.
-Absolutely. Absolutely.

00:21:55.300 --> 00:21:58.780
There were a lot of situations
where it did me more harm than good.

00:22:00.100 --> 00:22:06.420
I can be hasty, I can be harsh, I don't
have respect for people with authority,

00:22:07.140 --> 00:22:11.380
I don't admit when someone is better.
My friend told me once: "You wouldn't

00:22:11.580 --> 00:22:15.860
let a disabled person pass you on the
crosswalk, let alone anybody else."

00:22:16.100 --> 00:22:21.390
Whatever I do,
I try to be the best,

00:22:23.380 --> 00:22:32.413
and I enjoy messing with the people I
defeat, humorously undermining them.

00:22:34.700 --> 00:22:40.540
Let's move on from your childhood to
the first serious step in your career,

00:22:41.060 --> 00:22:46.126
a kind of turning point,
I would say so, and I think you'd agree.

00:22:46.299 --> 00:22:53.775
You went to Šabac in 1988/1989, where
this crazy generation was coming about.

00:22:54.000 --> 00:22:56.440
It was in 1978. -Yes, 1978.

00:22:58.500 --> 00:23:04.100
They called you aliens.
Please explain this project,

00:23:04.500 --> 00:23:09.740
the relationships within the city, the
club, the sponsors, Metaloplastika.

00:23:10.140 --> 00:23:15.140
I remember it even though
there is a big age gap here,

00:23:15.358 --> 00:23:19.093
but even to this day, when
Metaloplastika is mentioned

00:23:19.256 --> 00:23:22.296
in the world of handball,
it still holds a significant weight.

00:23:24.300 --> 00:23:28.100
I think I can describe
all of that in one sentence.

00:23:28.380 --> 00:23:33.780
I would trade 10 years of my life
now for 6 months from back then.

00:23:33.980 --> 00:23:35.580
That's how good it was?

00:23:37.220 --> 00:23:41.100
Maybe it was the carefree attitude
we had because of our youth,

00:23:41.290 --> 00:23:44.366
maybe it was the compatibility
between the teammates,

00:23:44.531 --> 00:23:48.531
maybe it was the results we had, maybe
it was the city's dedication to us...

00:23:48.639 --> 00:23:51.839
Or maybe it was all of that combined.
-Yes, all of that combined.

00:23:52.122 --> 00:23:59.741
When someone was sick or injured,
and I didn't manage to visit them,

00:24:00.100 --> 00:24:04.220
I felt like I wasn't even alive
that day. That's how it felt.

00:24:05.180 --> 00:24:09.180
The injured players would still be in
the stands to contribute in a way,

00:24:09.420 --> 00:24:14.980
make jokes and shout comments,
and keep the chemistry we had going.

00:24:17.500 --> 00:24:21.420
Thanks to the people who watched us,
we can live off of that high

00:24:21.700 --> 00:24:24.740
of those months to this day.
In the city, we're still highly

00:24:25.020 --> 00:24:31.740
valued and respected. Metaloplastika
still exists as a serious club.

00:24:32.140 --> 00:24:38.580
The city decided that Metaloplastika
can't disappear. It has to be financed,

00:24:38.820 --> 00:24:41.380
and no matter how little,
but it can't disappear.

00:24:41.620 --> 00:24:46.660
It happened to a lot of big clubs.
They completely disappeared.

00:24:46.900 --> 00:24:50.380
All of us players
remained in contact.

00:24:50.660 --> 00:24:56.300
But back then, 2 hours before the game,
the sports hall would be packed.

00:24:56.540 --> 00:25:03.980
You can't even imagine being teammates
with Isaković, with Vuković,

00:25:04.180 --> 00:25:07.820
Bašić, Portner, and Kuzmanovski.

00:25:09.420 --> 00:25:16.820
It was a privilege. -What ages were you?
Were you all close in age? -They were...

00:25:18.900 --> 00:25:23.300
Isaković, Vuković and Rašić
were born in 1958.

00:25:23.620 --> 00:25:27.140
Baško was born in 1960,
as well as Mrkonja.

00:25:27.340 --> 00:25:32.020
Portner was born in 1962, and I in 1961.
We were very close in age.

00:25:38.140 --> 00:25:43.860
Our sense of humor, professionalism,
our shooting hoops 3 vs 3...

00:25:44.260 --> 00:25:47.940
We would go to the morning stretching
session, and in the afternoons,

00:25:48.140 --> 00:25:51.860
we'd play Champions League game.
We were inseparable.

00:25:52.060 --> 00:25:56.589
The coach couldn't keep us apart,
and we'd fight him when he tried.

00:25:57.830 --> 00:26:00.222
It was something incredible.

00:26:01.380 --> 00:26:03.620
Mini football was on Mondays.

00:26:03.860 --> 00:26:08.340
We had a deal that if we won the match
on Saturdays, we'd play mini-football

00:26:08.580 --> 00:26:11.940
on Mondays. Out of the 80 games,
we won 79 annually.

00:26:12.180 --> 00:26:15.140
In the locker room
before the game, we'd say,

00:26:15.380 --> 00:26:19.140
"Let's be careful and not get injured.
We have mini-football on Monday".

00:26:19.620 --> 00:26:22.620
That was more "important"
to us than handball.

00:26:22.860 --> 00:26:26.620
Obviously, we were just
joking around to ease the tension.

00:26:28.460 --> 00:26:32.460
Isaković taught me
the first-step shot.

00:26:32.609 --> 00:26:34.976
He'd make me do it
for days on repeat

00:26:35.174 --> 00:26:38.750
so that when he would pass me the ball,
I could do a first-step shot.

00:26:38.920 --> 00:26:41.734
That move is what made
my whole career.

00:26:43.380 --> 00:26:47.220
When Baško would be
in front of the goal, he'd say:

00:26:47.876 --> 00:26:52.649
"If you throw the ball from there,
I have no way of defending it,"

00:26:53.165 --> 00:26:55.512
I thought, "If Bašić can't
defend this, then no one can."

00:26:55.711 --> 00:26:59.848
And then he would tell me, "If they
raise their arms, where can you shoot?"

00:27:00.012 --> 00:27:01.820
and I tell him, "I can only
shoot in that part there,"

00:27:01.901 --> 00:27:03.581
and he'd think to himself,

00:27:03.689 --> 00:27:06.203
"If Vujo can't score anywhere else
but there, then no one can."

00:27:06.393 --> 00:27:09.917
We helped each other be better,
we had discussions,

00:27:10.640 --> 00:27:15.370
we knew each other by heart. No words
needed to be exchanged in order for

00:27:15.760 --> 00:27:21.160
things to work on the court. And
above all, we were really good friends.

00:27:22.060 --> 00:27:26.780
That small place made it so that we
didn't have the kind of publicity

00:27:27.020 --> 00:27:29.260
we maybe would've had in Beograd,
but we had each other.

00:27:29.540 --> 00:27:35.140
Now, when I say small place, Šabac has
a population of 100.000/120.000 people,

00:27:35.420 --> 00:27:38.740
but then Našice, which has
a population of 10.000 people,

00:27:38.940 --> 00:27:41.220
makes me think that that's
what a small place actually is.

00:27:45.220 --> 00:27:48.860
But the whole organization...
For example, Aca Trifunović,

00:27:49.100 --> 00:27:52.980
who we've already mentioned,
never had written contracts for us.

00:27:53.220 --> 00:27:56.540
What were the finances like
at that time? -Amazing. Amazing.

00:27:56.980 --> 00:28:00.500
We were surely on the
same level as footballers.

00:28:00.740 --> 00:28:02.940
We also had premiums.

00:28:03.140 --> 00:28:06.100
They weren't tied to us winning
against somebody. That was silly.

00:28:06.380 --> 00:28:10.020
The premiums were based on who to beat
and with what difference in scores.

00:28:10.220 --> 00:28:15.820
Only then would we get our bonuses.
We never missed a single bonus.

00:28:16.060 --> 00:28:19.020
We got them all. It happened
very often that we would get

00:28:19.260 --> 00:28:21.900
just the right score needed for the
bonus. If it stated that we had to have

00:28:22.100 --> 00:28:25.820
a six-score difference against Zvezda,
we would get exactly that.

00:28:26.020 --> 00:28:30.340
I remember this one game
with IMT Rakovica.

00:28:30.660 --> 00:28:34.140
There were four minutes until the end,
and we need to win by nine goals.

00:28:34.380 --> 00:28:39.620
We rush to get it done in four minutes.
Everybody was rushing on the field,

00:28:39.900 --> 00:28:42.100
we were asking for timeouts, and people
were wondering what was up with us.

00:28:42.340 --> 00:28:45.220
In the end, we got
the nine-point difference.

00:28:45.460 --> 00:28:47.940
This one guy, Luka Božanić, who was
writing down statistics for the club,

00:28:48.140 --> 00:28:51.140
would say: "Guys, score 11 or 12...
But why exactly nine?"

00:28:51.380 --> 00:28:55.300
He hoped we would get an eight,
so the money would stay in the club.

00:28:56.180 --> 00:29:02.060
But it didn't start ideally. You came
in... -It didn't. The first year,

00:29:02.175 --> 00:29:04.855
we were fighting to survive.
-To survive? -Yes, to survive...

00:29:04.970 --> 00:29:08.690
Then, all of the younger players came in.
-That is right. We came because

00:29:08.796 --> 00:29:12.076
Sead "Hafa" Hasanefendić
made a suggestion.

00:29:12.284 --> 00:29:16.140
Portner, Mrkonja, and Bašić
all came into the club,

00:29:16.294 --> 00:29:19.663
and that's when it started. -In 1982, it
started to get better and never stopped.

00:29:19.813 --> 00:29:21.893
And it never stopped to this day.

00:29:22.340 --> 00:29:31.580
I don't know how to explain that.
All of it was normal and logical to me.

00:29:33.380 --> 00:29:36.980
I thought I was the best in basketball,
the best in handball, the best in this.

00:29:37.420 --> 00:29:41.980
Whatever I did, I thought I was the best
at it. I was awarded with the

00:29:42.070 --> 00:29:45.110
Popularity Award,
Best Sportsman in Yugoslavia Award,

00:29:45.178 --> 00:29:47.836
World Player of the Year Award,
and all of that was normal for me.

00:29:47.957 --> 00:29:49.517
I'm sorry for interrupting you.

00:29:49.592 --> 00:29:54.653
When was the first time
you felt that you were "the" guy?

00:29:55.860 --> 00:30:01.220
Did that happen in Metaloplastika
during the Yugoslavia championship

00:30:01.460 --> 00:30:05.060
and Champions League,
or did it come with the success of

00:30:05.340 --> 00:30:12.020
Olympic team? Which one was it?
-Ever since I was a kid, I have felt

00:30:12.260 --> 00:30:16.500
like I was better than everyone else.
You just have that feeling,

00:30:16.638 --> 00:30:19.078
especially when you have
the "Cetinje" mentality:

00:30:19.192 --> 00:30:21.072
even if you're not the best, you are.

00:30:22.740 --> 00:30:27.300
The Olympic games in Los Angeles.
I was 23 years old.

00:30:27.820 --> 00:30:31.580
There were a lot of other older players
there. I was one of the youngest ones.

00:30:31.860 --> 00:30:35.816
The late Branislav Pokrajac,
a genius,

00:30:36.820 --> 00:30:41.820
asked me if I realized that I was the
leader of that team. -And you were 23.

00:30:41.958 --> 00:30:44.678
I asked him what he meant
by saying I was the leader.

00:30:44.778 --> 00:30:47.298
He just said I was the leader,
that the team listened to me,

00:30:47.428 --> 00:30:51.920
and that I had to watch out for my
behavior, what I was saying and doing,

00:30:52.108 --> 00:30:55.236
because all of them
would be looking at me.

00:30:56.460 --> 00:30:59.780
I told him that was impossible,
and he said that we'll check it out.

00:30:59.945 --> 00:31:03.905
He said: "Tomorrow morning,
when you come to have breakfast,

00:31:04.340 --> 00:31:07.660
don't be the first one there,
but rather second.

00:31:07.940 --> 00:31:12.020
And don't sit next to the player
who was already there."

00:31:12.220 --> 00:31:15.340
Usually, you would come and see
a familiar face and sit next to them.

00:31:15.580 --> 00:31:19.054
I come to breakfast,
and Rnić was already there.

00:31:19.475 --> 00:31:21.835
I found another table and sat there.

00:31:23.103 --> 00:31:26.383
He called me a crazy man
and signaled to join him,

00:31:26.506 --> 00:31:29.249
but I told him I didn't like
his company, jokingly.

00:31:29.678 --> 00:31:32.335
Other players started coming in,
taking their plates, and soon enough,

00:31:32.454 --> 00:31:34.694
everybody started
taking a seat at my table.

00:31:34.804 --> 00:31:37.249
Only once the table was full,
they started joining Rnić.

00:31:38.203 --> 00:31:40.913
Pokrajac asked me
if I had seen what happened.

00:31:41.162 --> 00:31:44.210
I told him that wasn't fair since half
of the team was from Metaloplastika.

00:31:44.312 --> 00:31:46.936
He realized that I still
didn't believe him and told me:

00:31:47.995 --> 00:31:51.757
"Every night, in front of our
hotel in the Olympic Village,

00:31:51.998 --> 00:31:55.843
where all of the basketball, water polo,
and other players were hanging out,

00:31:56.012 --> 00:31:58.732
you will act like the main character,
joking around, talking...

00:31:58.995 --> 00:32:02.835
Since the curfew is at 11 pm,
you will go to bed 20 minutes earlier."

00:32:03.900 --> 00:32:07.136
I agreed to that. When it was 10:40,
and I wanted to go to my room,

00:32:07.283 --> 00:32:10.996
everybody asked me to stay longer. Five
minutes later, everybody else did, too.

00:32:11.102 --> 00:32:12.622
Nobody was outside.

00:32:12.736 --> 00:32:15.128
He said that now that I understand
my influence on others...

00:32:15.228 --> 00:32:18.028
Everything was clear. -... now you
have to be the leader and know how to

00:32:18.183 --> 00:32:21.129
lead your team. From that point on,
it was exactly like that.

00:32:21.300 --> 00:32:24.260
Then, I started thinking
during warmup sessions.

00:32:24.820 --> 00:32:30.460
I noticed that our goalkeepers
weren't touching the balls.

00:32:30.740 --> 00:32:34.140
I made a deal with some other players
to shoot the balls where they knew

00:32:34.460 --> 00:32:38.420
we would. That way, they would start
defending and get into the rhythm.

00:32:38.700 --> 00:32:41.900
They wouldn't be of any use to us
if they weren't in the zone.

00:32:42.180 --> 00:32:46.020
If I knew that some of my teammates
weren't in the best shape,

00:32:48.180 --> 00:32:54.900
I would start pushing them with
assists to help them break through.

00:32:55.980 --> 00:33:00.660
There were many things like those
throughout my career.

00:33:02.016 --> 00:33:05.192
During practices, I would also
give the team many ideas.

00:33:05.359 --> 00:33:08.575
I always knew I would be a coach.
I knew it from the first day.

00:33:08.772 --> 00:33:13.825
You did? -Yes, 100%. That drew me
in so much that it was unbelievable.

00:33:13.985 --> 00:33:16.145
A born leader. -Yes, but...

00:33:19.140 --> 00:33:23.940
Even today, I am fascinated by
prominent personalities making

00:33:24.140 --> 00:33:32.260
historical decisions and changing
thousands or millions of lives.

00:33:33.420 --> 00:33:37.300
For me, it is happening on a smaller
scale. I am making decisions about

00:33:37.540 --> 00:33:40.260
players and their positions.
Those are still important decisions,

00:33:40.500 --> 00:33:44.660
just like when you're making a list of
who to take to the Olympic games.

00:33:44.900 --> 00:33:48.900
With those decisions, you can
make or break someone's career.

00:33:49.180 --> 00:33:54.500
In all that, I tried to be
as fair as possible

00:33:54.980 --> 00:34:02.180
without being led by interests. I am a
strange guy, even when it comes to that.

00:34:04.860 --> 00:34:10.620
I am always observing and analyzing my
players. I watch them leaving the bus.

00:34:11.060 --> 00:34:15.780
Now, it is popular to wear headphones...
-All wearing Jordans... -Yes.

00:34:17.020 --> 00:34:20.540
And then you have our physician who has
a lot of those big things to carry.

00:34:20.820 --> 00:34:25.020
You see a player with his little bag
just walking by the physician.

00:34:25.260 --> 00:34:28.260
And then you see another player
with his own big luggage coming to

00:34:28.500 --> 00:34:32.380
help the physician. That's when
I know who is a fair player and

00:34:32.620 --> 00:34:35.340
is fit to be a part of a team sport.
It doesn't matter that the first player

00:34:35.580 --> 00:34:39.220
might play a bit better,
I will still choose the second one.

00:34:40.620 --> 00:34:45.500
That's how I go about things in my life.
I like people who give themselves to

00:34:45.700 --> 00:34:50.380
others and are willing to help.
I think that's the essence of life.

00:34:51.460 --> 00:34:56.620
To get back to that golden age.
It all began with the Olympics.

00:34:57.700 --> 00:35:02.780
Well, the Yugoslavia Championship was
for warming up and the Olympics came.

00:35:03.020 --> 00:35:07.580
Yes, in 1982, I was part of the national
team that won the bronze medal

00:35:07.820 --> 00:35:14.580
in the finals with Russia.
But I was the youngest of them all.

00:35:14.820 --> 00:35:19.700
At the time, I was playing with
Jurin, Rađenović, and Krivokapić.

00:35:20.820 --> 00:35:26.860
We won the junior world championship
in Portugal with Abaz Arslanagić.

00:35:27.460 --> 00:35:30.820
After that, we arrived at the airport,

00:35:31.660 --> 00:35:35.380
where we met the senior national
team heading to Switzerland.

00:35:36.540 --> 00:35:41.540
They just switched me from one flight
to the other. -You were doing a lot of

00:35:41.780 --> 00:35:50.420
things in parallel. -I came to some
sort of a combined national team.

00:35:50.740 --> 00:35:56.340
There were some amazing players there,
Jovičić, Božinović... There were really

00:35:56.580 --> 00:36:02.420
amazing, fantastic players. They
were giving out jerseys for the game.

00:36:03.540 --> 00:36:08.260
All the players were real jokesters
and then there was me, a kid.

00:36:08.780 --> 00:36:14.340
They gave me the number eight jersey
from Pavlo Jurin because I would be

00:36:14.580 --> 00:36:18.420
giving it back soon enough.
Pavle was in the military at the time.

00:36:18.700 --> 00:36:22.860
The meeting ended, and I stood at the
door and turned to them to say:

00:36:23.100 --> 00:36:27.300
"I will give Pavle his jersey back,
but I will take one of yours, for sure."

00:36:27.660 --> 00:36:32.197
Živković was panicking at the time.

00:36:34.220 --> 00:36:40.820
We played some games beneath our dignity,
with Switzerland, Romania, Bulgaria...

00:36:42.540 --> 00:36:46.900
They weren't giving their best.
But I was scoring left and right.

00:36:49.340 --> 00:36:54.420
At the time, there was no Internet
to see club player lists.

00:36:56.100 --> 00:37:00.820
The Yugoslavian sports magazine
said Pokrajac would publish the list

00:37:01.020 --> 00:37:05.980
in three days. Then, in two days...
Days felt like years.

00:37:06.380 --> 00:37:09.580
Finally, the title read,
"Pokrajac published the list."

00:37:09.780 --> 00:37:13.420
I opened the right page and
covered it with a piece of paper.

00:37:13.660 --> 00:37:17.740
I was slowly uncovering one-by-one
player on the list. -And?

00:37:18.540 --> 00:37:22.060
I couldn't find myself, but I ended up
being last on the list. -The last one?

00:37:22.300 --> 00:37:28.060
The last one. -My last name begins
with V, so... I was ecstatic.

00:37:28.260 --> 00:37:33.100
That euphoria, that craziness...
I can't even explain it to you.

00:37:35.740 --> 00:37:41.700
Back then, you couldn't read about the
dissatisfaction of the ones who didn't

00:37:41.940 --> 00:37:47.340
make it on the list because
there was a lot of respect there.

00:37:47.540 --> 00:37:50.820
Today, nobody pays attention
to the ones on the list,

00:37:51.100 --> 00:37:55.832
but goes straight to trashing the
selector because someone isn't there.

00:37:56.629 --> 00:37:58.869
That is what sales the papers.

00:37:59.112 --> 00:38:02.312
Back then, dare to say
something against the coach?

00:38:02.465 --> 00:38:04.980
You're out of your mind.
First, your parents would beat you,

00:38:05.137 --> 00:38:07.941
then the coaches at the club,
the presidents, and everyone else.

00:38:13.740 --> 00:38:18.340
Since we've came to that,
make a comparison for me

00:38:19.500 --> 00:38:23.780
between today's athlete
upbringing and ours.

00:38:23.980 --> 00:38:26.780
I consider myself
from the old generation.

00:38:27.020 --> 00:38:33.420
Let’s forget technological advancements,
mobile phones, and all that.

00:38:33.740 --> 00:38:38.700
How do you see it? How do coaches
and kids behave today,

00:38:38.940 --> 00:38:42.020
compared to before?
It's surely different.

00:38:42.300 --> 00:38:46.220
I was already
a serious national team player.

00:38:46.420 --> 00:38:50.740
When Pokrajac calls me to play
at the Balkan Championship,

00:38:50.980 --> 00:38:55.380
where we’re playing against Romania
or I don’t know who...

00:38:55.700 --> 00:39:03.285
I liked shooting high.
I see that in my players too.

00:39:04.140 --> 00:39:06.460
I try to correct that.

00:39:07.060 --> 00:39:11.460
I ask them how many shots
they've seen go over the goal.

00:39:11.700 --> 00:39:15.140
They say a lot. But how many
below the goal? They say none.

00:39:15.380 --> 00:39:18.060
The goal is down there.
Even if the shot isn’t perfect,

00:39:18.340 --> 00:39:22.660
the ball will go in, you understand?
Pokrajac tells me to shoot low.

00:39:22.860 --> 00:39:26.940
I shoot high. The goalkeeper saves it.
He tells me to shoot low.

00:39:27.180 --> 00:39:29.300
I shoot high again.
The goalkeeper saves it again.

00:39:29.500 --> 00:39:34.060
He calls me over to do 20 push-ups
if I want to play again.

00:39:34.300 --> 00:39:39.740
I sit on the bench. I think,
he's not going to make me do push-ups.

00:39:40.500 --> 00:39:44.460
Saković tells me to do the push-ups.
I think it over and lie down.

00:39:44.700 --> 00:39:51.060
Eight thousand people are counting.
One, two, three...

00:39:51.420 --> 00:39:54.180
They’re counting in Romanian.

00:39:54.420 --> 00:39:57.060
He puts me back in right after,
but the next shot goes low.

00:39:57.260 --> 00:39:59.660
That’s one of the details.

00:40:00.500 --> 00:40:03.940
Is that possible today?
-I don’t think it’s possible.

00:40:04.140 --> 00:40:07.340
A parent would immediately
come to complain,

00:40:07.540 --> 00:40:10.060
the newspapers would write about it.

00:40:10.260 --> 00:40:14.340
Journalists would attack the coach
for mistreating the players.

00:40:14.540 --> 00:40:17.900
How is it possible
for such a thing to happen?

00:40:18.220 --> 00:40:20.820
I would be called
into a meeting at the club,

00:40:20.927 --> 00:40:23.807
that this is not the behavior
of serious people...

00:40:23.951 --> 00:40:25.831
That’s handball today.

00:40:25.969 --> 00:40:28.729
Some people manage
in that environment, for sure.

00:40:29.660 --> 00:40:32.620
Maybe I’m a bit old-fashioned.

00:40:33.700 --> 00:40:40.700
Once I traveled to Minsk
with Zagreb handball players.

00:40:41.220 --> 00:40:45.980
When we landed, we didn’t
have roaming. It’s Belarus.

00:40:46.500 --> 00:40:51.820
We had to continue by bus.
400 kilometers.

00:40:52.060 --> 00:40:59.020
The whole way, they were playing
charades, word associations, singing.

00:40:59.220 --> 00:41:04.500
It was a joy to listen to them. Then we
arrived at the hotel and they found WiFi.

00:41:04.780 --> 00:41:07.860
No more camaraderie,
no more chatting or anything else.

00:41:08.380 --> 00:41:15.220
And it’s not just that. At one café
I saw a serious advertisement.

00:41:15.900 --> 00:41:19.900
"Come in, you can talk,
we don’t have WiFi."

00:41:20.300 --> 00:41:26.620
Four friends, each holding a phone.
Why did you even go out?

00:41:29.260 --> 00:41:33.220
Coaches used to be more like
volunteers-amateurs.

00:41:34.340 --> 00:41:37.020
They worked individually
with the players.

00:41:37.260 --> 00:41:41.260
Now it seems to me that
there isn't as much space.

00:41:41.740 --> 00:41:45.060
Or, how should I put it...
A handball school.

00:41:45.340 --> 00:41:49.700
Money, energy, or people?
What are we lacking?

00:41:50.220 --> 00:41:53.260
I always say that three things
are needed for success in sports.

00:41:53.420 --> 00:41:55.460
Cash, money, and funds.

00:41:55.700 --> 00:41:58.940
When you have those three,
everything goes smoothly.

00:42:01.140 --> 00:42:06.860
In the handball school,
I see short, tall, skinny, fat,

00:42:07.100 --> 00:42:12.300
boys, girls. The coach just gives
them a ball and they run.

00:42:12.980 --> 00:42:16.220
They haven’t worked
on some things.

00:42:16.335 --> 00:42:19.671
What matters is the
20 euros membership fee.

00:42:19.838 --> 00:42:22.118
Everything is superficial.
-It’s superficial.

00:42:22.340 --> 00:42:25.900
I’m not saying there aren’t people
who do it exceptionally well.

00:42:26.340 --> 00:42:31.460
It seems to me that
the handball federation

00:42:31.700 --> 00:42:35.740
needs to establish regulations
about handball schools.

00:42:36.300 --> 00:42:42.365
It seems to me that in handball
some rules haven’t been written down

00:42:44.193 --> 00:42:47.037
for how, what, when,
and at what age.

00:42:48.020 --> 00:42:51.620
The coach is there,
the kids show up,

00:42:51.860 --> 00:42:55.100
and he tells them to run
30 laps around the field.

00:42:55.300 --> 00:42:58.700
Why 30 laps?
What’s the purpose?

00:42:59.300 --> 00:43:02.500
To draw children in to love it,
to let them play first,

00:43:02.700 --> 00:43:05.620
so they are satisfied.
This way, some will give up.

00:43:05.820 --> 00:43:09.100
Half of them will give up
because of those 30 laps.

00:43:10.740 --> 00:43:14.380
In water polo, it's known.
First you swim,

00:43:14.620 --> 00:43:18.540
then you have to pull your arm out
and hold it above the surface

00:43:18.740 --> 00:43:21.700
for a certain amount of time,
then the rest.

00:43:21.940 --> 00:43:25.180
It’s the same in football.
That doesn’t exist in handball.

00:43:25.420 --> 00:43:28.900
When you think about how many serious
people and educators there are,

00:43:29.140 --> 00:43:35.220
you don’t have such an alphabet of sport.
Often it’s done at one’s discretion.

00:43:39.140 --> 00:43:45.140
When I was a coach in Zagreb, I insisted
that parents do not come to practice.

00:43:45.660 --> 00:43:49.660
I think they even wrote
that parents are forbidden to attend.

00:43:49.900 --> 00:43:57.540
Parents can sometimes have a bad
influence on their child’s development.

00:43:59.500 --> 00:44:02.940
There are parents who know
their child isn’t talented.

00:44:03.140 --> 00:44:06.540
But to keep them off the streets,
they direct them to sports.

00:44:06.669 --> 00:44:09.377
That’s correct,
as long as it’s possible.

00:44:10.979 --> 00:44:14.487
But there are those who are
sickeningly ambitious.

00:44:14.986 --> 00:44:17.674
They want their child
to be a tennis player.

00:44:17.860 --> 00:44:26.100
A survey was done in Serbia among
parents of boys who play tennis.

00:44:27.380 --> 00:44:34.580
"Would you agree for your children to
have a career like Troicki or Tipsarević?"

00:44:34.820 --> 00:44:37.340
Out of 100 respondents,
89 said no.

00:44:37.580 --> 00:44:40.860
The others want their child
to be like Đoković.

00:44:40.943 --> 00:44:43.063
Do you understand how far this goes?
-That’s the core of the problem.

00:44:43.147 --> 00:44:44.547
How far does it go?

00:44:46.660 --> 00:44:50.780
My son and my daughter
don’t play sports.

00:44:51.060 --> 00:44:53.980
I asked my son about handball.
"If I played handball,

00:44:54.220 --> 00:44:58.500
they would tell me, look how he plays,
and how his father played?"

00:44:58.740 --> 00:45:01.300
"I don’t need that."

00:45:02.740 --> 00:45:07.284
He played a bit of American football
until he suffered a serious injury.

00:45:09.860 --> 00:45:13.820
Sports didn’t interest
my daughter at all.

00:45:14.020 --> 00:45:18.060
She was born in Barcelona.
That’s a completely different mindset.

00:45:18.380 --> 00:45:20.500
Just take it easy.

00:45:21.420 --> 00:45:25.300
Let’s go back a bit
to the gold Olympic medal.

00:45:25.580 --> 00:45:30.100
I assume that’s the pinnacle for
everyone. Whoever experiences that...

00:45:30.460 --> 00:45:32.060
What’s happening?

00:45:32.729 --> 00:45:37.729
The Olympic Games in Los Angeles
were boycotted by Eastern countries.

00:45:38.180 --> 00:45:42.260
The Russians didn’t play,
nor the Poles, or East Germany.

00:45:43.140 --> 00:45:47.900
There was a stain
on that medal you won.

00:45:48.140 --> 00:45:52.100
You won the medal,
but the best weren’t there.

00:45:52.940 --> 00:45:55.500
That’s the first I’ve heard of it.

00:45:57.900 --> 00:46:01.580
But to participate in the Olympics...

00:46:03.060 --> 00:46:06.220
The World or European
Championship in any sport

00:46:06.460 --> 00:46:12.180
is just for that sport. At the Olympics,
there are athletes from all sports.

00:46:12.460 --> 00:46:18.260
It’s an incredible experience.
I remember spending

00:46:18.540 --> 00:46:26.940
a few hours next to Michael Jordan
waiting to go out for the opening.

00:46:28.500 --> 00:46:33.500
Yugoslavia was written with
a Y, like Yugoslavia.

00:46:34.140 --> 00:46:38.180
We were second to last,
and they were last in the parade.

00:46:39.980 --> 00:46:43.340
There were photo
opportunities, everything.

00:46:43.580 --> 00:46:48.020
Later you remember those details.

00:46:48.740 --> 00:46:53.540
There are Kićanović, Slavić.
They are legends.

00:46:53.860 --> 00:46:57.860
You experience eating
next to Teofilo Stevenson,

00:46:58.100 --> 00:47:01.220
maybe the greatest Cuban
boxer of all time.

00:47:01.460 --> 00:47:05.580
He eats next to you,
you can talk to him.

00:47:06.140 --> 00:47:12.420
When you win an Olympic medal...
When I won the medal,

00:47:13.060 --> 00:47:17.460
I felt an incredible emptiness.

00:47:19.700 --> 00:47:23.900
I thought about what more
I could achieve.

00:47:24.220 --> 00:47:26.900
Do you understand?
-That was a boost for you,

00:47:27.140 --> 00:47:30.700
only later came those 2-3 years
when everyone gathered.

00:47:30.980 --> 00:47:34.260
Then I told myself
that was the peak.

00:47:34.500 --> 00:47:38.620
My mother told me she wanted
me to climb my whole life,

00:47:38.860 --> 00:47:43.929
but to never reach the top.
I asked her why.

00:47:44.086 --> 00:47:47.390
"Son, from the top,
you can only fall down."

00:47:47.679 --> 00:47:51.429
I wondered if that was
the period when I would regress.

00:47:51.740 --> 00:47:55.780
Suddenly, you become a motivation
for everyone. Olympic champion.

00:47:56.180 --> 00:47:58.940
You have to behave that way,
put in the effort,

00:47:59.180 --> 00:48:01.660
because everyone wants
to beat you.

00:48:01.860 --> 00:48:07.420
Everyone wants to be better than you.
Then your stubbornness kicks in. No.

00:48:07.700 --> 00:48:13.540
That’s when the series of results starts.
-The culmination was in 1986.

00:48:13.780 --> 00:48:20.168
For seven years in a row,
I was the champion of Yugoslavia,

00:48:20.491 --> 00:48:24.971
five times in Spain, and for 12 years
I didn’t finish in second place.

00:48:26.220 --> 00:48:29.620
World champion? -Yes.
Olympic champion.

00:48:29.860 --> 00:48:31.820
What year was that?

00:48:32.140 --> 00:48:34.140
Kudos for this.
-Thank you.

00:48:34.460 --> 00:48:38.100
In a short period of time.
-That’s right. I was declared,

00:48:38.340 --> 00:48:41.620
as the only handball player,
the Athlete of the year.

00:48:41.820 --> 00:48:44.580
That was after 1986.
-That carries weight.

00:48:45.420 --> 00:48:51.620
Do you know why? Because in the
jury are those who were athletes.

00:48:51.820 --> 00:48:55.300
They aren’t journalists or anyone else.
Those who previously won

00:48:55.540 --> 00:48:59.260
the title of best athlete, they vote.
-Especially in this sport.

00:48:59.500 --> 00:49:03.820
It’s not football or basketball.
-After 1986 and the world championship,

00:49:04.060 --> 00:49:08.355
I played well in the world championship,
becoming Athlete of the year.

00:49:08.730 --> 00:49:13.500
The competition included
Dražen Petrović and Veselin Vujović.

00:49:14.140 --> 00:49:17.620
Dražen Petrović, do you know
what that is? An icon.

00:49:19.860 --> 00:49:26.060
They invite me there and I assume
if I’m invited, I’m the winner.

00:49:26.540 --> 00:49:31.060
But, a moment happened.
When I was going to school in Podgorica,

00:49:31.500 --> 00:49:34.340
the Montenegrin boxer,
Miodrag Perunović,

00:49:34.580 --> 00:49:37.900
who was the Athlete
of the year before me,

00:49:39.580 --> 00:49:43.820
boxed in an incredible way.
With so much heart and desire,

00:49:44.060 --> 00:49:49.180
with so much fighting spirit.
I wanted to get into TV set.

00:49:49.420 --> 00:49:52.820
For nine minutes,
the match lasted, I cried.

00:49:53.060 --> 00:49:57.820
To give him my strength, my heart,
just to endure that match.

00:50:00.260 --> 00:50:04.700
We came to the voting,
and the wotes of the jury are read.

00:50:04.900 --> 00:50:10.580
I think to myself, if he didn’t vote
for me, I won’t accept this award.

00:50:10.780 --> 00:50:14.300
He is obligated to vote for me!

00:50:14.460 --> 00:50:17.140
That’s the mentality.
-He owes me that.

00:50:17.740 --> 00:50:23.180
They read, Franjo Mihalić
for Dražen Petrović.

00:50:23.460 --> 00:50:26.260
Dražen Dalipagić
for Veselin Vujović.

00:50:26.460 --> 00:50:30.460
Miroslav Cerar for Petrović,
Vera Nikolić for Veselin Vujović.

00:50:30.660 --> 00:50:33.300
Miodrag Perunović...
I hold my breath.

00:50:34.020 --> 00:50:37.820
For Veselin Vujović.
That’s it. -That’s it. -It’s done.

00:50:38.620 --> 00:50:44.294
I experienced that very emotionally.
Later, I was in that jury as well.

00:50:45.983 --> 00:50:51.505
I regret that it stopped
for some reason.

00:50:53.500 --> 00:50:56.882
Country became smaller.

00:50:58.500 --> 00:51:01.980
At that time, Yugoslavia was
a breeding ground for athletes.

00:51:02.220 --> 00:51:07.220
Can you imagine a handball team
from the former Yugoslavia?

00:51:07.700 --> 00:51:11.780
I’ve been asked several times
to assemble

00:51:12.020 --> 00:51:17.060
the ideal seven from all the players
from this region.

00:51:23.300 --> 00:51:29.300
I tell them I can’t. Seven?
No chance. How to choose seven?

00:51:32.660 --> 00:51:35.140
It’s the same in all other sports.

00:51:35.380 --> 00:51:39.820
I believe that if that
country had survived,

00:51:40.740 --> 00:51:44.420
Europe would have wanted
to play in our leagues. -Yes.

00:51:44.820 --> 00:51:47.420
In all sports.
-Yes, in all sports.

00:51:50.740 --> 00:51:56.020
With the award I received
for the Olympic Games,

00:51:56.540 --> 00:52:00.460
I bought a color TV.
That was the award.

00:52:00.900 --> 00:52:06.460
I think I even had to pay extra.
At that time, color TVs came out.

00:52:06.940 --> 00:52:11.787
And now it's similar when it
comes to state awards.

00:52:12.540 --> 00:52:15.116
In Serbia, it's different.
-A little better?

00:52:15.300 --> 00:52:17.220
Not a little, but much better.

00:52:17.700 --> 00:52:22.260
I think in individual sports,
it's 30 thousand euros or more.

00:52:22.700 --> 00:52:27.980
Maybe it's even 50.000 in individual,
and in team sports, everyone gets 30.

00:52:28.300 --> 00:52:35.260
We also have national recognition.
-That exists in Croatia too.

00:52:35.359 --> 00:52:37.559
That’s three average salaries.

00:52:38.260 --> 00:52:41.540
The Serbian government
pays that regularly.

00:52:41.940 --> 00:52:45.820
That’s a very big deal.
Maybe not for most of those people

00:52:46.060 --> 00:52:50.980
who have their own companies, but there
are people who have had problems.

00:52:51.220 --> 00:52:54.380
That money meant a lot to them.

00:52:55.860 --> 00:53:04.140
That’s when I bought a color TV.
That was in '82, '84, '86, and '88.

00:53:05.140 --> 00:53:10.300
European titles with the club,
world championships,

00:53:11.940 --> 00:53:18.100
Popularity Award. I got that too.
I still have it. TV magazine.

00:53:18.300 --> 00:53:22.940
Miroslav Ilić, Neda Ukraden,
and I among them.

00:53:23.980 --> 00:53:29.140
Guests at the concert of Isaković,
at the concert of Đorđe Balašević.

00:53:30.100 --> 00:53:32.660
Do you know what that is?
That’s an incredible feeling.

00:53:32.900 --> 00:53:35.140
The fulfillment of all dreams.

00:53:36.380 --> 00:53:40.980
After that,
my Achilles tendon ruptured.

00:53:41.893 --> 00:53:46.973
At the peak of fame. -What year?
-My Achilles tendon ruptures.

00:53:47.080 --> 00:53:48.811
That was 1987.

00:53:54.340 --> 00:54:02.060
I read the columns you wrote.
-1986-1987, we play against Rostock,

00:54:03.060 --> 00:54:06.580
Champions League in Šabac.
I turn to run and feel

00:54:06.820 --> 00:54:12.099
as if someone hit me.
I see there’s no one around.

00:54:12.474 --> 00:54:17.998
I think something hit me. No.
I see a hole and there’s no tendon.

00:54:18.278 --> 00:54:23.053
I have a recording of that,
everyone chants "God help."

00:54:23.923 --> 00:54:27.163
I go to the hospital.
-That’s 27-28 years ago.

00:54:27.347 --> 00:54:30.384
You’re ready for abroad.

00:54:31.837 --> 00:54:38.111
When the ball is won, from
point A to point B, I see no obstacle.

00:54:38.187 --> 00:54:40.255
It seems to me that no one
can hold me back.

00:54:40.359 --> 00:54:41.919
That’s incredible.

00:54:43.580 --> 00:54:46.660
I wondered why this
happened to me.

00:54:46.940 --> 00:54:53.140
At that time, an Achilles tendon injury
meant the end in 99% of cases.

00:54:54.740 --> 00:54:58.500
Your whole world collapsed.
-Telegrams started coming.

00:55:00.060 --> 00:55:09.140
From the company "13. Jul,"
from Macedonia, from Zenica, INA.

00:55:11.940 --> 00:55:16.580
Workers from that company
decided to cover the costs

00:55:16.860 --> 00:55:19.500
of the operation for Veselin Vujović
anywhere in the world.

00:55:19.740 --> 00:55:25.100
Houston, Moscow, anywhere.
I received over 30 such telegrams.

00:55:25.980 --> 00:55:29.300
I have them all. I decided to have
the operation in Šabac.

00:55:29.940 --> 00:55:32.860
Who operated on me?
Nebojša Popović.

00:55:33.140 --> 00:55:36.700
One of the best handball players
that our country has produced.

00:55:36.940 --> 00:55:41.020
He was an expert on knees.
He had never operated

00:55:41.220 --> 00:55:46.020
on any Achilles tendon.
But I wanted him to operate on me.

00:55:46.540 --> 00:55:52.180
On the day of the operation,
it may sound a bit strange,

00:55:53.420 --> 00:55:59.260
a man died and on that body
he practiced how to cut.

00:55:59.900 --> 00:56:02.460
That was his model.

00:56:04.180 --> 00:56:10.460
I asked him what percentage
of 100 patients recovers.

00:56:10.940 --> 00:56:14.820
He told me one or two.
I said I'm the one.

00:56:15.380 --> 00:56:17.420
Again, the mentality.

00:56:18.740 --> 00:56:22.780
The operation is not the problem.
Recovery is the biggest problem.

00:56:23.020 --> 00:56:25.660
But even during that,
I had incredible treatment.

00:56:25.900 --> 00:56:29.860
Workers from the Borovo company,
a shoe factory,

00:56:31.060 --> 00:56:36.420
made a special shoe
for me with a raised heel.

00:56:36.740 --> 00:56:41.500
You keep your foot elevated,
so the tendon remains shorter.

00:56:41.900 --> 00:56:46.020
Then you have to raise the heel,
women know that.

00:56:46.260 --> 00:56:50.820
I would walk like that
for maybe 10 days.

00:56:51.300 --> 00:56:58.140
Then I went to the shoemaker and
he lowered the heel half a centimeter.

00:56:58.540 --> 00:57:03.580
I walked like that again, trying not
to make any sudden movements

00:57:03.780 --> 00:57:09.140
so the tendon wouldn’t rupture again.

00:57:10.820 --> 00:57:14.900
After that I went
to Igalo to recover.

00:57:15.700 --> 00:57:18.660
I worked with Minja Bulut,
a phenomenal therapist.

00:57:18.900 --> 00:57:23.300
There were swimming pools,
salt water, skip, walking...

00:57:23.580 --> 00:57:28.260
After the Achilles tendon injury,
I had a better recovery

00:57:28.500 --> 00:57:32.740
than any athlete in the world.
-How did you feel mentally?

00:57:32.940 --> 00:57:36.900
Were you depressed, feeling bad, or
were you always thinking positively?

00:57:37.100 --> 00:57:40.700
I constantly had
a feeling that the tendon

00:57:40.940 --> 00:57:43.820
would burst again
if I made any movement.

00:57:46.140 --> 00:57:52.540
It was summer,
we played basketball in Budva.

00:57:53.020 --> 00:57:55.780
But I was still saving
myself, dragging my foot.

00:57:56.020 --> 00:57:59.620
There were many guys
from Budva there,

00:58:03.700 --> 00:58:06.881
and there was great
competition in the game.

00:58:07.069 --> 00:58:10.669
There was also a great rivalry between
people of Budva and us from Cetinje.

00:58:11.420 --> 00:58:14.700
My brother, godfather and I
were playing,

00:58:15.100 --> 00:58:19.300
and at one point there was a fight.
Was it a traveling or not?

00:58:19.980 --> 00:58:23.180
And then a guy who was watching
everything said: "There was no traveling."

00:58:23.380 --> 00:58:25.780
I answered him:
"Who asked you?"

00:58:27.060 --> 00:58:29.940
I turned around and said to
a guy I knew was in control

00:58:30.180 --> 00:58:32.900
of that group of guys: "Calm
down these guys of yours."

00:58:33.140 --> 00:58:36.820
Then I turned around and saw
that that boy had hit my brother.

00:58:37.660 --> 00:58:40.340
In that moment,
a stampede occurred.

00:58:40.580 --> 00:58:44.860
50 people began to fight.
That was something unprecedented.

00:58:45.780 --> 00:58:47.980
I ran after that guy.

00:58:48.220 --> 00:58:51.460
There was one canal that took
waste water into the sea,

00:58:51.660 --> 00:58:54.420
which was quite wide.

00:58:54.740 --> 00:58:59.460
Running after him, I jumped
over it without any problem.

00:58:59.582 --> 00:59:01.771
I reached him and then...
I won't go into details.

00:59:01.861 --> 00:59:03.941
Maybe I shouldn't
have told this either.

00:59:04.534 --> 00:59:06.681
When I calmed down
and everything was over,

00:59:06.857 --> 00:59:09.056
I realized that I don't have
that fear anymore.

00:59:09.218 --> 00:59:12.555
Imagine the moment that
brings me back to normal.

00:59:12.944 --> 00:59:15.742
An abnormal moment
brings me back to normal.

00:59:16.445 --> 00:59:19.085
Of course we solved all that.

00:59:19.276 --> 00:59:21.755
Even today, I have
many friends in Budva.

00:59:21.876 --> 00:59:25.016
I'm even friends with the guy
who initiated everything

00:59:25.355 --> 00:59:28.880
and we laugh when we talk about it.
That's an anecdote.

00:59:31.180 --> 00:59:38.500
While I was in my sickbed,
a telegram from Barcelona arrived.

00:59:40.300 --> 00:59:43.020
It read: "To our player",

00:59:43.260 --> 00:59:45.860
although I have not signed
or agreed anything,

00:59:46.060 --> 00:59:49.220
"we want a speedy recovery."

00:59:50.620 --> 00:59:53.220
Was it the first
contact with Barcelona?

00:59:53.460 --> 00:59:55.140
You heard something for sure.

00:59:55.380 --> 01:00:00.820
Kalin who already played in Barcelona
called me, but it was nothing concrete.

01:00:05.260 --> 01:00:09.420
We played against Barcelona
in the Champions League.

01:00:11.780 --> 01:00:18.780
Then Isaković and Vuković left...
Metaloplastika was allegedly in decline.

01:00:19.420 --> 01:00:27.820
While we were playing against Barcelona,
we, taught by bad experiences,

01:00:28.060 --> 01:00:32.860
asked for bottled water
that hadn’t been opened.

01:00:34.020 --> 01:00:37.300
I wondered if the bottle I was
drinking from had been opened,

01:00:37.460 --> 01:00:39.260
but I drank the water anyway.

01:00:39.540 --> 01:00:44.060
After that I developed a fever
and was taken to the hospital.

01:00:45.460 --> 01:00:49.700
I got an IV there, but the
temperature did not drop.

01:00:50.100 --> 01:00:52.660
The game was about to start
and I was still in the hospital.

01:00:52.860 --> 01:00:55.980
Then I told them I was going.

01:00:56.860 --> 01:01:00.500
Although there was opposition,
I showed up at the match.

01:01:01.180 --> 01:01:05.340
We played well in the first half,
but in the end we lost by 6 points.

01:01:05.900 --> 01:01:11.740
I was very angry, and I was always
a leader and an authority figure.

01:01:13.260 --> 01:01:18.420
At that moment, I said to my
teammates: "Don't let anyone

01:01:18.700 --> 01:01:24.140
make a statement to the newspaper,
to anyone, at any time.

01:01:25.060 --> 01:01:29.020
You are not allowed to leave
the house for seven days."

01:01:29.340 --> 01:01:34.340
"But we have to,
our children are here," they said.

01:01:34.580 --> 01:01:37.700
No leaving the house
for seven days.

01:01:37.900 --> 01:01:41.060
You can only go to the gym
and to your apartment.

01:01:41.460 --> 01:01:44.340
During the seven days,
no one broke that rule.

01:01:44.580 --> 01:01:46.380
After that we are "broke" Barcelona.

01:01:46.580 --> 01:01:50.300
We were leading by 11-12 points,
and in the end, we eliminated them.

01:01:50.500 --> 01:01:53.100
And if you watch the footage
of that game, you'll see those players

01:01:53.300 --> 01:01:55.660
running up to me and hugging me.

01:01:55.860 --> 01:01:59.060
They knew that I did it
for the good of all of us.

01:01:59.300 --> 01:02:03.500
I didn't go out for
those seven days either.

01:02:03.740 --> 01:02:06.180
I knew I needed to be focused.

01:02:06.380 --> 01:02:11.180
Then, when I destroyed Barcelona,
that first contact actually happened,

01:02:11.420 --> 01:02:13.900
then the tendon ruptured,
after which I thought

01:02:14.140 --> 01:02:17.780
I was saying goodbye to everything.
-But they are calling again? -Yes.

01:02:17.980 --> 01:02:20.900
Yes, they call, send telegrams,
but there is also a call

01:02:21.100 --> 01:02:23.420
for mandatory military service came.

01:02:23.700 --> 01:02:27.580
I could get rid of that,
because I had a serious injury.

01:02:27.780 --> 01:02:31.220
I would receive a certificate, which
would release me from this obligation.

01:02:31.500 --> 01:02:34.580
But, Krsto Vujović,
my father said:

01:02:34.860 --> 01:02:38.660
"Son, no one was exempt from military
service in the Vujović household,

01:02:38.860 --> 01:02:42.220
so neither will you be.”
I said, "But, dad..." "No discussion!"

01:02:42.460 --> 01:02:45.060
"If you are not fit for the army,
then you are not fit for sports,

01:02:45.300 --> 01:02:49.380
nor for marriage, nor anything."
God, what am I going to do?

01:02:50.140 --> 01:02:54.620
So, I went to Kraljevo, where my
sergeant  was a certain Patarić,

01:02:55.460 --> 01:02:57.860
whom I knew from
Pogorica as a coach.

01:03:00.220 --> 01:03:06.660
During my military service,
Colonel Boteri allows me

01:03:07.140 --> 01:03:15.380
to go to the Mataruška spa
by army car, Pinzgauer, to recover.

01:03:15.940 --> 01:03:21.540
And the army, the people's army,
helped me a lot to recover.

01:03:22.300 --> 01:03:26.660
Then representatives of
Barcelona came to my garrison.

01:03:27.100 --> 01:03:29.820
They came while you were
in the army? -That's right.

01:03:30.580 --> 01:03:35.660
The president of the handball section
Fraciscoo Ventura and Valero Rivera came.

01:03:36.620 --> 01:03:38.660
Valero has been there before?
-Yes.

01:03:38.900 --> 01:03:41.580
And Milan Kalina
as a translator.

01:03:42.180 --> 01:03:46.580
We generally agreed that
I would come to Barcelona.

01:03:46.780 --> 01:03:48.620
You don't have a manager?
You negotiated directly?

01:03:48.900 --> 01:03:51.540
I directly agreed to
come to Barcelona.

01:03:51.740 --> 01:03:54.540
It was more of a verbal
agreement, so to speak.

01:03:55.860 --> 01:03:58.420
It was a transfer, of all transfers?
-That's right.

01:03:59.100 --> 01:04:03.420
It was worth some then
70-80 thousand dollars.

01:04:03.980 --> 01:04:06.060
It was nothing special.

01:04:06.300 --> 01:04:10.820
But... Veselin Vuković
played for Atletico Madrid.

01:04:11.180 --> 01:04:16.660
He called me and said: "Forget
Barcelona, ​​come to Madrid."

01:04:18.180 --> 01:04:20.900
I remembered that he had called me
even when I was in Šabac

01:04:21.100 --> 01:04:23.980
and said the same thing.
He decided my fate.

01:04:24.220 --> 01:04:27.660
I decide to go to Madrid.

01:04:28.660 --> 01:04:31.900
When Kalina called me, I said
that I had already agreed

01:04:32.140 --> 01:04:34.180
with the people from Madrid.
-"So how, why", he asked?

01:04:34.380 --> 01:04:37.060
I said: "Sorry."

01:04:37.300 --> 01:04:41.620
The president of the club
and Vuković came from Madrid

01:04:41.820 --> 01:04:46.716
and I signed a preliminary contract.
I don't even know what I signed.

01:04:47.135 --> 01:04:49.495
Now it was already 150.000.

01:04:54.460 --> 01:04:59.340
Then Kalina called me and asked
if I had signed the Fica federativa.

01:04:59.660 --> 01:05:02.420
That's the gateway.
I replied that I didn't.

01:05:02.620 --> 01:05:04.540
We will come to
your place tomorrow.

01:05:04.780 --> 01:05:08.020
I said: "Don't!" He answered:
"We are coming tomorrow..."

01:05:08.340 --> 01:05:13.230
When he came,
Valero now offered 250,000.

01:05:13.799 --> 01:05:16.058
That had to be thought about. -Yes.

01:05:18.300 --> 01:05:24.500
Vuković then told me: "You have
a call from Jesus Gil on the other line."

01:05:24.740 --> 01:05:29.860
He was the genius
president of Atletico Madrid.

01:05:30.220 --> 01:05:32.460
"HFe will talk to you."

01:05:33.020 --> 01:05:36.540
He was speaking in Spanish so
I had no idea what he was talking about.

01:05:36.686 --> 01:05:41.246
Vuković told me that they want
me there, they want me to play there

01:05:41.368 --> 01:05:44.328
and no matter how much Barcelona
offers me, they will offer more.

01:05:44.464 --> 01:05:46.424
My God, save me...

01:05:48.060 --> 01:05:51.020
After we finished that
conversation, Kalina answered.

01:05:51.300 --> 01:05:53.820
Please are you free at
5 PM because the president

01:05:54.060 --> 01:05:56.700
of Barcelona Jose Luis Nunes
wants to talk to you?

01:05:56.980 --> 01:05:59.340
He said: "No matter how much
Atlético Madrid offered you,

01:05:59.540 --> 01:06:05.980
we will offer more." I'm already
starting to feel ashamed.

01:06:06.180 --> 01:06:10.820
I couldn't bid any more,
I had to stop.

01:06:12.620 --> 01:06:15.821
I then called my wife
from the barracks and told her:

01:06:15.965 --> 01:06:18.282
"Please help me, because
I can't make a decision."

01:06:18.444 --> 01:06:20.117
Tell me what to do."

01:06:20.260 --> 01:06:22.220
She said: "Vujo,
people from Barcelona

01:06:22.368 --> 01:06:26.165
contacted you when no one
knew if you would recover.

01:06:26.816 --> 01:06:32.209
They believed you would.
I think it's still a better decision."

01:06:32.467 --> 01:06:34.507
And that was the verdict?

01:06:34.860 --> 01:06:41.580
Valero and Kalina came again and
I told them how much money I wanted.

01:06:42.060 --> 01:06:45.060
I want for Metaloplastika
150.000 compensation.

01:06:45.340 --> 01:06:48.660
How many years will I be in the club,
they have to pay for the preparations.

01:06:48.900 --> 01:06:51.060
It's a million dollar transfer.

01:06:51.580 --> 01:06:55.580
Valero and Kalina said
that they cannot decide on that,

01:06:55.820 --> 01:07:01.020
but they have to talk to the president
who is on vacation in Palma de Mallorca

01:07:01.300 --> 01:07:06.900
to see what he will decide.
Valero told me about it later.

01:07:07.100 --> 01:07:12.980
Nunes hooked some apron
a Valero was completely professional,

01:07:13.180 --> 01:07:17.940
he doesn't want to hold
a grudge against anyone.

01:07:18.380 --> 01:07:23.420
He told him that the transfer
will cost almost a million

01:07:24.780 --> 01:07:26.980
and that we cannot sign that contract,

01:07:27.180 --> 01:07:31.165
because we have many
footballers that we pay less.

01:07:31.761 --> 01:07:35.314
Nunes' wife was listening to all this.

01:07:36.820 --> 01:07:39.700
At that moment, Jesús Gil
bought a little pony

01:07:39.980 --> 01:07:44.420
and named it José Luis Nunes
to insult him.

01:07:44.700 --> 01:07:50.060
She was angry that he was insulting him
and that he was going to take me to Madrid.

01:07:50.300 --> 01:07:55.260
She asked Valero: "What is that
player like?" He answered: "The best."

01:07:55.540 --> 01:07:57.540
"Is he worth that much?
He is worth."

01:07:57.740 --> 01:08:00.220
I will give the money for him.

01:08:00.460 --> 01:08:04.860
Actually, she is the one who
gave the money for my transfer.

01:08:05.100 --> 01:08:07.980
Later when we would go on trips,
because she had no idea,

01:08:08.260 --> 01:08:14.020
she would ask: "Is this one mine?"
I would answer: "Yes, that's me."

01:08:17.700 --> 01:08:22.460
There is another anecdote.
The president called me Vuho.

01:08:23.060 --> 01:08:26.340
Once I told him: "It's not
Vuho president, it's Vujo."

01:08:26.485 --> 01:08:29.380
And he answered me: "Listen, please,
there is Real Madrid goalkeeper

01:08:29.514 --> 01:08:33.468
Paco Buyo and your name reminds me
of him, so I can't call you that."

01:08:33.561 --> 01:08:36.929
I said: "Okay, call
me Pepe if you want."

01:08:38.718 --> 01:08:40.382
So it's a wonderful period.

01:08:45.340 --> 01:08:47.020
I want some comparison.

01:08:47.260 --> 01:08:52.580
You played for the two strongest teams
in the world, Metaloplastika and Barcelona.

01:08:53.140 --> 01:08:56.140
Compare those cities
and the game for me.

01:08:56.380 --> 01:08:59.860
When the Champions League was played,
where was the better celebration.

01:09:00.100 --> 01:09:02.700
In Barca or Šabac?

01:09:02.980 --> 01:09:05.980
You cannot compare Šabac
and Barcelona as cities.

01:09:06.220 --> 01:09:12.020
Nor history or culture, etc.
Šabac was emotion, love...

01:09:12.198 --> 01:09:16.158
Šabac was something that makes
you happy at all times.

01:09:16.232 --> 01:09:18.192
The first? -That's right.

01:09:19.260 --> 01:09:23.660
Barcelona was an organization,
wealth, splendor, power...

01:09:24.820 --> 01:09:29.780
When you win the title you go out on
Nou Camp in front of 100.000 people.

01:09:29.960 --> 01:09:34.632
Before the match, you go out to the
balcony and the same greeting follows.

01:09:34.980 --> 01:09:38.374
You know you'll get a bonus, money
will be deposited into your account.

01:09:38.787 --> 01:09:43.515
Sun, sea... - Yes, that was
the most beautiful period of my life.

01:09:44.620 --> 01:09:48.580
But I also felt enormous pressure
and pressing in Barcelona.

01:09:49.020 --> 01:09:51.500
There is no other,
you have to be first.

01:09:51.740 --> 01:09:55.900
You have to be the best.
There are no comparisons.

01:09:56.140 --> 01:09:58.580
You know what you're here for...

01:09:58.780 --> 01:10:02.860
We play a game in which we win
by 10-15 points, and I play 60 minutes.

01:10:03.060 --> 01:10:07.443
I ask Valera: "Okay, well,
why don't you give me a break?"

01:10:07.940 --> 01:10:13.020
Listen, if I take you out, the audience
will slowly start to leave the hall.

01:10:13.340 --> 01:10:16.460
But as long as you're on the field,
they expect you to do something

01:10:16.740 --> 01:10:20.300
that makes them think it's okay
that they came to watch you.

01:10:21.660 --> 01:10:26.820
So when you get a load, carry it.
There is no emotion here, that's clear.

01:10:30.900 --> 01:10:35.100
But that welcome to Šabac,
when we won the title.

01:10:36.740 --> 01:10:41.900
At the Belgrade airport, 30-40 thousand
people were waiting for us

01:10:42.180 --> 01:10:43.940
The column of cars was almost
from the airport to Šabac,

01:10:44.140 --> 01:10:47.180
maybe the whole of Šabac.

01:10:48.700 --> 01:10:51.674
Maybe there was there
100-120 grand people.

01:10:51.812 --> 01:10:54.471
Now someone will ask why I
say thousands and grand?

01:10:54.626 --> 01:10:56.290
It's the same for me.

01:11:00.100 --> 01:11:05.020
It was a collapse from the bridge
to the hall, something incredible.

01:11:05.740 --> 01:11:09.540
And in Garnier, when we won
the Euro Cup with both

01:11:09.820 --> 01:11:14.340
Barcelona and Vardar, it was nice,
but I will never forget

01:11:14.620 --> 01:11:19.980
that first welcome with Metaloplastika.
That was something special.

01:11:20.300 --> 01:11:22.860
That was among my people.

01:11:23.140 --> 01:11:27.060
My wife put my son in my arms
over the fence,

01:11:27.980 --> 01:11:33.620
there was my neighbor, my godfather.
Nothing can change that feeling.

01:11:34.940 --> 01:11:39.940
When you played in Barcelona,
​​and we all know what Barcelona is,

01:11:40.180 --> 01:11:43.380
a whole team with multiple sports,
were there people from this region?

01:11:43.580 --> 01:11:47.180
Who did you hang out with?
Did you have someone close?

01:11:47.420 --> 01:11:50.980
They were in the basketball club.
Boža Majković and Zoran Savić.

01:11:54.740 --> 01:11:59.300
Handball club had Portner
and Vuković with me.

01:12:01.340 --> 01:12:04.420
In other sports,
Željko Obradović in Joventut,

01:12:04.660 --> 01:12:09.340
Ljupko Petrović in Espanyol, Milanović
and Andrić in the water polo club.

01:12:09.620 --> 01:12:14.420
It was a serious colony
of Yugoslavs. We all hung out.

01:12:14.940 --> 01:12:20.260
In general, that was at my place. I had an
really large apartment and a huge terrace.

01:12:22.620 --> 01:12:26.460
And were you
connected with football?

01:12:26.660 --> 01:12:29.340
and other sports, like basketball?

01:12:30.140 --> 01:12:36.260
In Castell de Fels,
it's a coastal place,

01:12:36.540 --> 01:12:40.740
one member of the
board had his own club.

01:12:42.220 --> 01:12:44.620
It was a restaurant,
pool and beach.

01:12:44.900 --> 01:12:50.260
And we athletes Barcelona we had
the privilege of being able to go there.

01:12:50.500 --> 01:12:53.780
We didn't pay for parking,
the price of food was normal, etc...

01:12:54.020 --> 01:13:00.660
And we often hung out with Johan Cruyff,
who has a special life philosophy.

01:13:02.420 --> 01:13:06.700
I exchanged, then there were cassettes,
with the famous Hristo Stoichkov.

01:13:06.900 --> 01:13:08.780
Hristo Stoichkov!

01:13:09.020 --> 01:13:12.180
He gave me a cassette of Miroslav Ilić,
and I gave him a cassette of Lepa Brena.

01:13:12.420 --> 01:13:15.940
Michael Laudrup was also there.

01:13:16.180 --> 01:13:20.980
Together, they were just recovering
from injuries at that Medico service.

01:13:21.220 --> 01:13:25.540
We had good relations
and before every game

01:13:25.820 --> 01:13:29.180
they would leave us twenty
tickets for football matches

01:13:29.500 --> 01:13:32.300
in the dressing room,
if we wanted to watch them.

01:13:32.580 --> 01:13:36.620
When it was a little colder, and
they give us those seats at the top,

01:13:36.860 --> 01:13:40.140
where it is dangerously windy,
I said I would watch the game at home.

01:13:40.380 --> 01:13:43.258
When Vuković came to see me
in Barcelona, ​​he would dress warmly

01:13:43.424 --> 01:13:45.648
and watch, because
he thought it was cool.

01:13:45.728 --> 01:13:48.000
He would say: "Is it possible
that you are not watching,

01:13:48.093 --> 01:13:50.460
and there it is, only 50 meters away?"
Because I lived nearby.

01:13:50.667 --> 01:13:53.539
Even today, I support
the football and handball

01:13:53.693 --> 01:13:55.883
club Barcelona and I am
really a big fan of them.

01:13:57.860 --> 01:14:01.460
Now let's move on to the
coaching career, because,

01:14:01.700 --> 01:14:05.780
Vujo, we need 3-4 hours for your career,
so we have to speed it up a bit.

01:14:06.020 --> 01:14:09.140
I didn't tell you many
anecdotes or details

01:14:09.380 --> 01:14:12.060
or some things, because
we wouldn't get there.

01:14:12.300 --> 01:14:15.940
You have rich experience.
-You will also have to cut something.

01:14:16.460 --> 01:14:22.580
In Greniers, I decided to end
my career  at the age of 34.

01:14:23.180 --> 01:14:26.500
I am quitting.
I turned into a fridge.

01:14:26.740 --> 01:14:30.959
Ice on the knee, ice on the
shoulder, ice on the tendon.

01:14:32.061 --> 01:14:34.146
You feel when it's over.

01:14:34.540 --> 01:14:39.060
We won the European title
at the Plaza de Mallorca,

01:14:39.340 --> 01:14:43.780
where 30-40 thousand people chanted:
"Stay one more year."

01:14:44.020 --> 01:14:46.700
You know how it goes.

01:14:47.380 --> 01:14:53.820
I said I would stay whenever
they offered me a two-year contract.

01:14:54.060 --> 01:14:56.180
But when they offer me a year,
it means that

01:14:56.420 --> 01:14:59.100
they also think that
I have reached my limit.

01:14:59.260 --> 01:15:01.140
That's why I won't
play that last year.

01:15:01.340 --> 01:15:04.060
I wanted people to remember me
as a great sportsman,

01:15:04.300 --> 01:15:07.340
and not to say how I dragged
myself around the field.

01:15:07.620 --> 01:15:11.540
I returned to Šabac and immediately
became a coach of Metalopalstika.

01:15:12.340 --> 01:15:14.820
Without days of coaching experience,
without anything,

01:15:15.020 --> 01:15:18.100
I immediately became Tuta Živković's
assistant in the national team.

01:15:18.420 --> 01:15:23.260
Metaloplastika played well,
I had a good projection as a coach.

01:15:25.140 --> 01:15:27.900
At 34 years old, straight from sneakers
to coach and assistant coach

01:15:28.140 --> 01:15:30.540
of the national team?
-That's right.

01:15:32.020 --> 01:15:36.140
I also worked well as a coach
of some junior national teams

01:15:36.460 --> 01:15:41.940
and I really developed in that direction
and it went fantastically well for me.

01:15:42.220 --> 01:15:47.740
Everything was progressing great
when I got a call from Pick Szeged.

01:15:51.018 --> 01:15:56.060
I went to Szeged and after the conversation
decided to take over Pick Szeged.

01:15:56.820 --> 01:16:00.980
When I was returning, my cell
phone rang at the border crossing.

01:16:02.620 --> 01:16:10.260
Jesus Revilla calls me from Siudad Real
and asks if you would be our coach?

01:16:10.900 --> 01:16:15.020
Man, Spain, my language, history...

01:16:16.220 --> 01:16:21.100
I call these people from Szeged
to tell them I gave them my word.

01:16:21.340 --> 01:16:26.146
This is my wish, but if you insist,
I will stay and be your coach.

01:16:27.100 --> 01:16:32.220
They say: "You are already
in Spain in your mind.”

01:16:32.860 --> 01:16:35.500
I am going to Siudad Real.

01:16:39.780 --> 01:16:42.140
That lasted half a season.

01:16:42.526 --> 01:16:46.086
Then the second season starts,
we bring players.

01:16:46.780 --> 01:16:52.100
We are making a story
for something bigger.

01:16:53.060 --> 01:16:56.620
Something you write
in golden letters.

01:16:56.799 --> 01:16:59.159
I am very glad about that.

01:17:00.940 --> 01:17:08.140
The cup final against Flensburg
is coming. -What year? 2002, 2003?

01:17:08.340 --> 01:17:12.460
I don't know...
Flensburg is coming...

01:17:16.340 --> 01:17:21.140
And a few years ago, they played
Challenge Cup, with Flensburg.

01:17:21.420 --> 01:17:24.380
A draw at home,
and they were overjoyed.

01:17:24.620 --> 01:17:27.580
The rematch came and they
convincingly beat them.

01:17:27.820 --> 01:17:32.900
They were even unpleasant.
They provoked them at a reception.

01:17:33.460 --> 01:17:40.140
So, the players were in a subordinate
position. Somehow they were afraid.

01:17:40.420 --> 01:17:46.060
Now, I put myself first.
Like, I'll be able to undo it.

01:17:46.580 --> 01:17:49.380
The space is full, chaos...

01:17:49.780 --> 01:17:52.540
In the first half,
they lead by one goal.

01:17:52.780 --> 01:17:55.580
I enter the dressing room,
grab them by the neck.

01:17:55.820 --> 01:18:00.048
How many finals have you played?
Come on, wake up!

01:18:00.671 --> 01:18:03.384
We're back in the second half.

01:18:03.830 --> 01:18:07.251
Their coach is Danish,
a fantastic player and coach.

01:18:07.740 --> 01:18:14.060
He is constantly walking in the area,
reserved for judges. Nobody reacts.

01:18:14.900 --> 01:18:20.974
I go over and push him.
The crowd starts cheering.

01:18:22.340 --> 01:18:28.860
1, for us, 2, 3, 5 7, 8...
Mariano Ortega scores 8th goal.

01:18:29.940 --> 01:18:34.220
I understood it as a personal struggle,
alone against everyone.

01:18:34.700 --> 01:18:38.363
Mariano Ortega scores
a goal and falls.

01:18:38.800 --> 01:18:43.460
When he fell, a German or Danish
player fell on him.

01:18:44.220 --> 01:18:50.740
A mess ensues. I'm running there,
because we don't need chaos.

01:18:51.500 --> 01:18:57.820
Bogdan Veta is grabbing me,
he was afraid of my character.

01:18:59.571 --> 01:19:06.254
He rips my shirt and I take
it as an attack on me.

01:19:07.908 --> 01:19:12.930
The players come up to me
and I hit them one by one.

01:19:13.200 --> 01:19:17.206
A classic fight? -No, I hit them,
but nobody hits me back.

01:19:19.460 --> 01:19:23.180
Once that's over, the referees
don't record anything.

01:19:23.420 --> 01:19:26.580
But the Germans, of course,
reported me to the EHF

01:19:26.860 --> 01:19:29.420
and punished me for 16 months.

01:19:29.740 --> 01:19:32.500
I am complaining, they are
punishing me another 2 years.

01:19:33.700 --> 01:19:38.060
Usually, the appeal is confirmed, but
they punish me for another 2 years.

01:19:41.460 --> 01:19:49.140
We are traveling to Germany
and some neo-Nazi groups

01:19:49.620 --> 01:19:52.820
are threatening me that I will not
be allowed to enter the hall

01:19:53.100 --> 01:19:55.980
and that there will be reprisals.

01:19:56.500 --> 01:20:00.340
We are in the hotel.
I'm getting ready.

01:20:00.620 --> 01:20:06.980
I call my brother from Hamburg.
He will come with 3-4 huge friends.

01:20:07.220 --> 01:20:10.740
They are two meters high, huge.

01:20:10.980 --> 01:20:13.780
Brother, let's see who
will deny you entry?

01:20:14.020 --> 01:20:15.900
When Domingo Diaz saw them...

01:20:16.140 --> 01:20:18.700
"Vujo, could you please,
don't let them go,

01:20:18.940 --> 01:20:21.980
because the players will react.

01:20:22.180 --> 01:20:26.740
He will try to defend himself.
Please, you stay at the hotel."

01:20:27.580 --> 01:20:33.070
We have a phone connection.
Watch the game and make moves.

01:20:34.940 --> 01:20:38.460
The vice president stays
with me and I agree to that.

01:20:39.540 --> 01:20:41.300
And what is happening?

01:20:41.580 --> 01:20:46.140
Schumacher drives and the Germans
don’t participate in handball.

01:20:46.380 --> 01:20:50.580
The match has started, but I can't
watch the match. I'm going crazy.

01:20:52.020 --> 01:20:57.300
I am calling my wife who is in
Spain, she watch the match.

01:20:57.820 --> 01:21:00.060
I ask her about the result.

01:21:00.300 --> 01:21:06.860
She says 5:1. "How?",
I ask her: "Who scores goals?"

01:21:07.220 --> 01:21:13.460
She says:
"He is beautiful, the Dane."

01:21:15.060 --> 01:21:19.780
Who plays against him?
She says: "Pogorelov".

01:21:20.940 --> 01:21:24.860
I tell her to put Ortega
on two, as a defense.

01:21:25.220 --> 01:21:29.700
I run the match with my
wife, using the phone.

01:21:29.940 --> 01:21:34.380
The second half was on.
We win the title.

01:21:34.820 --> 01:21:37.980
I tell the president
and everyone knows.

01:21:38.180 --> 01:21:41.620
We get awards, we celebrate...

01:21:41.860 --> 01:21:50.540
They call my wife and give her a watch.
Like, she deserves the title.

01:21:53.500 --> 01:21:57.660
They tell me: "Vujo, you have been
punished and you can’t play."

01:21:58.780 --> 01:22:02.940
Juan Dios is coming,
and I'm coming to Serbia.

01:22:03.420 --> 01:22:07.060
I am becoming the head coach
of Serbia and Montenegro.

01:22:08.140 --> 01:22:10.860
There were competitions
and world championships.

01:22:11.100 --> 01:22:14.500
Again, it’s at a very good level.
I am head coach at all levels.

01:22:15.060 --> 01:22:19.340
For junior, senior and
cadet national teams.

01:22:19.540 --> 01:22:24.460
We were declared as the best
EHF national team in the world,

01:22:27.380 --> 01:22:31.460
because we were fourth
at the World Cup.

01:22:32.220 --> 01:22:36.340
Juniors were second in the world,
cadets champions of Europe.

01:22:36.540 --> 01:22:40.300
All in all, we were the best.

01:22:40.540 --> 01:22:43.820
Also, I receive medal
"The Merit to the Nation".

01:22:46.940 --> 01:22:51.940
In all this, Serbia and
Montenegro are separated.

01:22:52.940 --> 01:22:55.860
Serbia would like me
to remain the coach of Serbia,

01:22:56.020 --> 01:22:58.620
and Montenegro wants the same.

01:22:58.860 --> 01:23:02.860
Difficult time... -Whatever I decide,
I will have a problem.

01:23:02.951 --> 01:23:07.271
And then, I go to Macedonia,
to Vardar, to Mihajlo Mihajlovski.

01:23:12.300 --> 01:23:14.060
One question?

01:23:14.620 --> 01:23:19.180
Siudad Real is the club
where I collected the cream.

01:23:19.420 --> 01:23:23.460
I have a feeling that this
happened in Vardar as well.

01:23:23.740 --> 01:23:28.060
You made a team. Someone else
won the Champions League.

01:23:28.380 --> 01:23:32.340
That's my feeling.
-I didn't mean to say that.

01:23:33.140 --> 01:23:37.780
I never had a good team,
with serious players.

01:23:38.260 --> 01:23:43.319
I had to deal with the mining
all the time.

01:23:44.340 --> 01:23:49.020
I only had a great generation
in Zagreb, when I took over.

01:23:49.300 --> 01:23:54.060
These were: Stepančić, Šebetić,
Mandalinić, Pavlović, Valčić...

01:23:54.340 --> 01:23:57.940
And then we played a fantastic
Champions League.

01:23:58.380 --> 01:24:02.420
You played in the quarter finals.
-I had to work hard for everything else.

01:24:02.660 --> 01:24:06.340
I was at Siudad Real,
it’s my own fault, I stand by that.

01:24:06.500 --> 01:24:09.060
Are you sorry? -I'm very sorry.

01:24:09.340 --> 01:24:15.380
I think my career would be totally
different, on a different level.

01:24:16.140 --> 01:24:19.660
After that incident, my way
to Germany was closed.

01:24:19.860 --> 01:24:24.780
I had a contact, I was planned
to take over Fuchse Berlin.

01:24:25.060 --> 01:24:29.828
But I made an incident
with the German club.

01:24:30.580 --> 01:24:36.700
I'm going to Vardar.  Six years
is the fight against Metalurg,

01:24:36.900 --> 01:24:40.940
Lino Červar, madness.
They are champions, then we...

01:24:41.380 --> 01:24:43.180
Incredible history.

01:24:44.420 --> 01:24:49.079
Metalurg is making progress,
they are investing a lot of money.

01:24:49.956 --> 01:24:51.501
Mihajlo tells me:

01:24:51.650 --> 01:24:56.993
"A Russian has appeared.
He wants to invest in the club."

01:25:00.401 --> 01:25:05.837
I asked him from 0 to 100%,
how much he would provide.

01:25:06.120 --> 01:25:09.020
He said it would be 100%.
He invests so much.

01:25:10.420 --> 01:25:15.020
We have a meeting tomorrow
that I have to attend.

01:25:15.300 --> 01:25:19.780
I also came to the meeting,
Samsonenko is there, Mihajlo, too.

01:25:20.060 --> 01:25:25.663
At first glance, I didn't like him.
He had a lukewarm greeting.

01:25:27.288 --> 01:25:32.820
He started saying that he wanted
to bring Lacković, Šterbik...

01:25:33.060 --> 01:25:37.460
I ask him why he wants that?
He better bring Landin...

01:25:37.980 --> 01:25:43.060
And I continue to list younger players
at the end of their careers.

01:25:43.385 --> 01:25:47.338
He says: "I want to people
know about me!" I tell him:

01:25:47.900 --> 01:25:52.238
"When you have money, people
know about you, don't worry."

01:25:54.465 --> 01:25:58.820
He tells me:
"My coaches listen to me."

01:26:00.140 --> 01:26:04.180
I answer him: "You don't know
the circumference of the ball,

01:26:04.302 --> 01:26:06.822
nor the dimensions of the field.

01:26:07.180 --> 01:26:10.600
If I'm your coach,
draw a line and you say:

01:26:10.737 --> 01:26:12.777
"Vujović, you did a good job.

01:26:12.884 --> 01:26:14.724
The results are good,
and so is the end.

01:26:14.949 --> 01:26:19.029
But don't tell me, who will play,
I don't allow that."

01:26:19.860 --> 01:26:23.460
He stood up, muttered something,
said goodbye to Mihajlo and left.

01:26:23.700 --> 01:26:26.644
Mihajlo tells me that it will be difficult
to reach an agreement with him.

01:26:26.909 --> 01:26:31.246
But I don't want
an agreement with him.

01:26:33.300 --> 01:26:37.940
It is a shame that he interferes
in the work of some coaches.

01:26:38.140 --> 01:26:41.460
And he is sitting on the bench.
That's really funny.

01:26:42.420 --> 01:26:45.620
And then came that golden time.
Lots of money, good players, everything.

01:26:45.860 --> 01:26:49.060
And something similar again
in Siudad Real, but I wasn't there.

01:26:50.260 --> 01:26:56.020
Maybe that's my destiny...
-But that came back with Slovenia?

01:26:58.340 --> 01:27:03.020
Suddenly, a specific match.
I was in Croatia.

01:27:03.300 --> 01:27:05.580
That's terrible, you were losing...

01:27:06.100 --> 01:27:09.340
If you ask me how I won,
I can't explain.

01:27:09.580 --> 01:27:12.580
And surely even Babić
doesn't know how he lost.

01:27:13.100 --> 01:27:16.700
In some analysis,
which may not be accurate,

01:27:17.340 --> 01:27:23.140
I said at the meeting
that Croatia was in a shock.

01:27:23.420 --> 01:27:27.460
Zlaja Horvat missed a penalty,
in the last second against Norway.

01:27:27.740 --> 01:27:29.940
You played after us,
you were tired.

01:27:30.180 --> 01:27:36.500
We will run and try to fight.  Running
is not a problem for Slovenians, is it?

01:27:38.220 --> 01:27:40.940
How long will it all take?

01:27:41.500 --> 01:27:45.980
We get into a position where
we are nowhere, we don’t exist,

01:27:46.180 --> 01:27:48.620
for the first 15 minutes.

01:27:52.300 --> 01:27:56.140
Croatia leads, succeeds.
-It was 52nd minute 7, 8 difference.

01:27:56.620 --> 01:28:00.540
I come to the dressing room
and I ask them do they know

01:28:00.820 --> 01:28:05.060
that thousands
and thousands of people

01:28:05.340 --> 01:28:11.194
are watching them at home,
their hearts are beating for them?

01:28:11.659 --> 01:28:17.364
Isn't it a shame to play them like this?
Why don't they fight to the death?

01:28:17.980 --> 01:28:20.820
Then it will be written somewhere
that they died bravely:

01:28:21.060 --> 01:28:24.980
Veselin Vujović, Jure Dolenec,
Marko Bedželić...

01:28:25.260 --> 01:28:27.620
And then someone will remember it.

01:28:27.820 --> 01:28:31.780
Will you arrive at the airport and run
away without anyone noticing you?

01:28:32.380 --> 01:28:37.700
That had no effect.
They lead by 7 or 8 goals.

01:28:38.700 --> 01:28:43.460
I think, I'm the only fool, I’m jumping
around and making excuses.

01:28:45.060 --> 01:28:47.820
But I remember that I got
a contract for two years.

01:28:48.060 --> 01:28:50.340
How am I going to get those
guys back?

01:28:50.580 --> 01:28:54.180
I will manage the game as if
there is only a 2 goal difference.

01:28:54.580 --> 01:28:57.900
When we reduced the score,
I said: "Let's do two more."

01:28:58.300 --> 01:29:02.500
And what is happening?
If Babić had put in Šebetic, Mihić,

01:29:02.740 --> 01:29:05.860
and these youngsters,
who were on the bench,

01:29:06.060 --> 01:29:13.460
they would have run over us.
He still held Cindrić, Duvnjak, Štrlek,

01:29:14.380 --> 01:29:17.900
who were too tired even
before this match.

01:29:18.500 --> 01:29:22.580
When we started to reduce the result,
it was too late for him to take risks

01:29:22.860 --> 01:29:26.620
and then we start to run
and get control.

01:29:26.940 --> 01:29:34.020
And in the end it ends the way it did.
It is an extremely emotional moment,

01:29:34.540 --> 01:29:39.780
when that people and
that country was in question.

01:29:40.180 --> 01:29:44.380
Even that reception, which was
organized in the best possible way.

01:29:44.620 --> 01:29:49.460
Heads are falling in our country at
that time. It was difficult in Croatia.

01:29:51.380 --> 01:29:54.980
When one goes down,
someone goes up.

01:29:55.580 --> 01:29:58.660
Slovenians hired me
because of my character.

01:29:58.900 --> 01:30:02.780
In the end, they were bothered
by my character, but that's who I am.

01:30:03.220 --> 01:30:07.740
A transparent man.
When I'm in the mood, I smile.

01:30:07.940 --> 01:30:11.435
When I'm angry, it shows on me.
I don't know how to foil.

01:30:11.794 --> 01:30:16.500
That, may be,
my good or bad quality.

01:30:16.780 --> 01:30:22.260
But that's me, a transparent person.
And I will always be like that.

01:30:22.900 --> 01:30:25.460
I appreciate human values.

01:30:25.700 --> 01:30:31.780
I want to die on my feet,
not on my knees.

01:30:32.700 --> 01:30:37.420
And this decision I made is based
on my life philosophy.

01:30:38.420 --> 01:30:42.180
Voja, we've reached the very end.

01:30:43.020 --> 01:30:46.460
Time is running out,
I still have many questions.

01:30:46.700 --> 01:30:49.060
This is the final question.

01:30:49.340 --> 01:30:52.300
When you draw the line,
after player career

01:30:52.540 --> 01:30:55.460
and the coach's career still lasts.

01:30:56.140 --> 01:31:04.940
Is there any regret, failure, sadness,
something in your entire career?

01:31:05.135 --> 01:31:07.572
Is there anything
you would like to change?

01:31:07.725 --> 01:31:09.965
Most say:"I wouldn't change anything".

01:31:10.228 --> 01:31:13.908
We all have something that
bothers us. Do you have that?

01:31:14.305 --> 01:31:18.185
I would change all these stupid
and things I did,

01:31:18.307 --> 01:31:20.331
thanks to my character.

01:31:20.700 --> 01:31:24.839
Sometimes, when I watch videos,
I think I'm not normal.

01:31:25.047 --> 01:31:28.727
You mean Siudad Real?
-And long before that.

01:31:31.580 --> 01:31:34.580
Barcelona is my unfulfilled wish.

01:31:34.820 --> 01:31:40.220
When Eric Massip became the director,
we agreed that I would be the coach.

01:31:40.500 --> 01:31:46.020
But then Valero Rivera came in charge,
and we were not getting along.

01:31:47.100 --> 01:31:49.980
He didn't accept me
as a coach in Barcelona.

01:31:51.260 --> 01:31:54.380
This is a big failure
and a big wish for me.

01:31:54.620 --> 01:31:58.940
Of course, I no longer harbor illusions
that I will be the coach of Barcelona.

01:31:59.140 --> 01:32:01.580
I'm seriously old.

01:32:02.180 --> 01:32:08.260
Then I made a couple of mistakes
while moving to Željezničar from Niš,

01:32:08.540 --> 01:32:11.180
or Borac from Banja Luka.

01:32:11.580 --> 01:32:14.420
These are mistakes in sport,
not human.

01:32:14.660 --> 01:32:21.660
But, there I met wonderful people,
players, who I will remember all my life.

01:32:21.900 --> 01:32:30.740
Those are some sporting failures.
All these are great experiences for me.

01:32:31.020 --> 01:32:36.060
A good result and
success follow me.

01:32:38.540 --> 01:32:43.380
People often think that with
my knowledge and my name,

01:32:43.580 --> 01:32:47.540
I will extract of quality from them.
I have to think like other coaches.

01:32:47.740 --> 01:32:50.180
Assemble the team
as I want and can,

01:32:50.380 --> 01:32:53.260
and only then do I bear
the responsibility.

01:32:53.500 --> 01:32:58.380
Taking responsibility for other
people's mistakes is really difficult.

01:32:58.740 --> 01:33:02.260
That happened to me
both in Niš and Banja Luka.

01:33:02.500 --> 01:33:06.780
But life is a road
with a thousand crossroads.

01:33:08.215 --> 01:33:12.420
And you always have to decide
whether to go straight, left or right.

01:33:12.660 --> 01:33:16.860
If no one advises you, you must
be making a mistake somewhere.

01:33:16.989 --> 01:33:19.109
It is not always possible to guess.

01:33:19.540 --> 01:33:24.540
Dear Voja, it was a pleasure
to listen to you.

01:33:24.860 --> 01:33:29.740
Thank you for the pleasant company
and honesty in the interview.

01:33:29.980 --> 01:33:33.180
I wish you a quick engagement
and lots of luck in life.

01:33:33.280 --> 01:33:34.720
Thank you very much.

